WEBVTT

00:00:22.752 --> 00:00:26.756 line:90% position:50% align:center
We are overjoyed that you are
among the millions around the world

00:00:26.756 --> 00:00:30.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
who are viewing this convention.

00:00:30.217 --> 00:00:33.220 line:90% position:50% align:center
An infirm Bible student named Joyce,

00:00:33.220 --> 00:00:35.514 line:90% position:50% align:center
who lives in Southeast Asia,

00:00:35.514 --> 00:00:40.102 line:90% position:50% align:center
expressed her appreciation
for these arrangements by saying:

00:00:40.102 --> 00:00:43.731 line:90% position:50% align:center
“With the convention being streamed online,

00:00:43.731 --> 00:00:47.276 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I don’t have to miss a single talk!

00:00:47.276 --> 00:00:51.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I can watch the program
with the rest of the brotherhood worldwide.

00:00:51.656 --> 00:00:55.827 line:90% position:50% align:center
I am so thankful to Jehovah
for this arrangement.”

00:00:56.911 --> 00:01:00.164 line:90% position:50% align:center
Perhaps you can relate to her expressions.

00:01:01.290 --> 00:01:05.253 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you for the generous donations
you have made online

00:01:05.253 --> 00:01:10.008 line:90% position:50% align:center
at donate.jw.org and by other means,

00:01:10.008 --> 00:01:13.344 line:90% position:50% align:center
which help make
these streaming services possible.

00:01:15.847 --> 00:01:18.516 line:90% position:50% align:center
During these critical last days,

00:01:18.516 --> 00:01:20.768 line:90% position:50% align:center
many families lack the affection

00:01:20.768 --> 00:01:25.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah designed us to give and receive.

00:01:25.106 --> 00:01:28.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, God’s Word contains principles

00:01:28.526 --> 00:01:31.946 line:90% position:50% align:center
that, when followed, lead to peace.

00:01:33.364 --> 00:01:37.911 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re sure you will enjoy
the fine talks and dramatizations

00:01:37.911 --> 00:01:40.914 line:90% position:50% align:center
in this next symposium.

00:01:40.914 --> 00:01:44.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
Brother Joel Dellinger,
a helper to the Service Committee,

00:01:44.668 --> 00:01:46.961 line:90% position:50% align:center
will deliver the first talk,

00:01:46.961 --> 00:01:51.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Follow the Road Map to Family Peace
—Show Love and Respect.”

00:02:00.225 --> 00:02:03.061 line:90% position:50% align:center
Family peace is precious.

00:02:03.061 --> 00:02:05.730 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s even as the Bible proverb says:

00:02:05.730 --> 00:02:09.442 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Better is a piece of dry bread
where there is peace

00:02:09.442 --> 00:02:13.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
than a house full of feasting
along with quarreling.”

00:02:13.572 --> 00:02:16.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what exactly is family peace?

00:02:17.075 --> 00:02:21.997 line:90% position:50% align:center
Someone might say, “As long as we’re not
arguing, our family is at peace.”

00:02:21.997 --> 00:02:24.499 line:90% position:50% align:center
But is that real peace?

00:02:24.499 --> 00:02:27.669 line:90% position:50% align:center
We might think of two countries
that were fighting

00:02:27.669 --> 00:02:30.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
but have now agreed to a cease-fire.

00:02:30.088 --> 00:02:32.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
Does the cease-fire mean that they’ve become

00:02:32.549 --> 00:02:35.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
real friends who love one another?

00:02:35.260 --> 00:02:36.803 line:90% position:50% align:center
No.

00:02:36.803 --> 00:02:40.515 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know that genuine peace takes more work.

00:02:40.515 --> 00:02:43.060 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s true in the family as well.

00:02:43.060 --> 00:02:47.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our heavenly Father knows
that the most satisfying family peace

00:02:47.856 --> 00:02:51.026 line:90% position:50% align:center
involves more than an absence of arguing.

00:02:51.026 --> 00:02:55.197 line:90% position:50% align:center
It involves a family’s well-being and unity.

00:02:56.406 --> 00:03:00.869 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is such peace in a family today
really possible?

00:03:01.829 --> 00:03:06.166 line:90% position:50% align:center
Although none of us have a perfect family,
the answer is yes.

00:03:06.166 --> 00:03:09.753 line:90% position:50% align:center
While it requires work
—perhaps breaking bad habits

00:03:09.753 --> 00:03:13.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
that disrupt peace and adopting
new ones that promote it—

00:03:13.215 --> 00:03:15.759 line:90% position:50% align:center
those efforts are worth it.

00:03:16.594 --> 00:03:18.679 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this symposium,

00:03:18.679 --> 00:03:23.684 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’ll see how Bible principles
can guide families to peace,

00:03:23.684 --> 00:03:25.686 line:90% position:50% align:center
just as a road map

00:03:25.686 --> 00:03:29.064 line:90% position:50% align:center
guides travelers to a beautiful destination.

00:03:29.064 --> 00:03:33.527 line:90% position:50% align:center
In each of the talks,
we invite you husbands, fathers,

00:03:33.527 --> 00:03:37.323 line:90% position:50% align:center
wives, mothers, children, teenagers

00:03:37.323 --> 00:03:40.159 line:90% position:50% align:center
to be the traveler who studies the map

00:03:40.159 --> 00:03:43.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then goes in the right direction.

00:03:43.287 --> 00:03:45.289 line:90% position:50% align:center
The focus of our first talk

00:03:45.289 --> 00:03:49.001 line:90% position:50% align:center
is showing love and respect.

00:03:49.001 --> 00:03:52.338 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why would you say these two qualities

00:03:52.338 --> 00:03:55.466 line:90% position:50% align:center
are so important to family peace?

00:03:55.466 --> 00:03:57.468 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, it’s simple:

00:03:57.468 --> 00:04:00.721 line:90% position:50% align:center
because family members
who love and respect one another

00:04:00.721 --> 00:04:03.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
feel secure and appreciated.

00:04:03.391 --> 00:04:06.060 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a result, our relationships

00:04:06.060 --> 00:04:09.981 line:90% position:50% align:center
are warm, close, and peaceful.

00:04:09.981 --> 00:04:14.777 line:90% position:50% align:center
Of course, showing love and respect
can be a challenge these days.

00:04:14.777 --> 00:04:17.697 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the following dramatization notice why.

00:04:21.033 --> 00:04:23.035 line:90% position:50% align:center
Irene.

00:04:24.871 --> 00:04:25.913 line:90% position:50% align:center
Aww,

00:04:25.913 --> 00:04:27.623 line:90% position:50% align:center
you look so handsome there.

00:04:27.623 --> 00:04:30.335 line:90% position:50% align:center
Oh, you look beautiful.

00:04:30.335 --> 00:04:32.337 line:90% position:50% align:center
Those came out so nice.

00:04:33.546 --> 00:04:35.340 line:90% position:50% align:center
Look at you.

00:04:36.716 --> 00:04:37.759 line:90% position:50% align:center
Crazy, right?

00:04:37.759 --> 00:04:38.635 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s the day!

00:04:39.344 --> 00:04:40.303 line:90% position:50% align:center
Look at us.

00:04:40.303 --> 00:04:41.804 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re so surprised.

00:04:41.804 --> 00:04:43.473 line:90% position:50% align:center
I just knew you were going to do it.

00:04:43.723 --> 00:04:44.807 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sorry, Olivia.

00:04:44.807 --> 00:04:45.850 line:90% position:50% align:center
Are you OK?

00:04:45.850 --> 00:04:46.851 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, it’s OK, Sue.

00:04:46.851 --> 00:04:48.144 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m so sorry.

00:04:48.144 --> 00:04:49.062 line:90% position:50% align:center
No worries.

00:04:49.062 --> 00:04:50.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
Um, I’m all moved in.

00:04:50.522 --> 00:04:52.440 line:90% position:50% align:center
That was the last box.

00:04:54.609 --> 00:04:55.902 line:90% position:50% align:center
Dad, are those the wedding photos?

00:04:55.902 --> 00:04:56.444 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:04:56.444 --> 00:04:57.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let me see.

00:04:57.779 --> 00:04:58.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
Look it. Here’s . . .

00:04:58.947 --> 00:05:01.032 line:90% position:50% align:center
Oh, you all look beautiful.

00:05:01.032 --> 00:05:01.866 line:90% position:50% align:center
That dress looks so nice.

00:05:01.866 --> 00:05:02.784 line:90% position:50% align:center
You look so good.

00:05:03.159 --> 00:05:04.327 line:90% position:50% align:center
Aww, look at you.

00:05:04.327 --> 00:05:06.371 line:90% position:50% align:center
Aww, that suits you.

00:05:06.371 --> 00:05:08.373 line:90% position:50% align:center
Very nice, you guys.

00:05:08.373 --> 00:05:09.958 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, it all came together.

00:05:09.958 --> 00:05:11.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
It really did.

00:05:11.084 --> 00:05:11.918 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:05:24.431 --> 00:05:25.891 line:90% position:50% align:center
Olivia?

00:05:27.017 --> 00:05:29.102 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know this is all new, baby.

00:05:29.978 --> 00:05:31.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be patient.

00:05:40.489 --> 00:05:41.823 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can I cut in?

00:05:41.823 --> 00:05:43.116 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, sure.

00:05:44.910 --> 00:05:46.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thanks.

00:06:07.140 --> 00:06:08.475 line:90% position:50% align:center
What’s wrong?

00:06:08.934 --> 00:06:10.435 line:90% position:50% align:center
Where’s the desk?

00:06:10.435 --> 00:06:12.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
We had to get rid of it.

00:06:12.771 --> 00:06:14.815 line:90% position:50% align:center
This one is better for everyone.

00:06:14.815 --> 00:06:16.650 line:90% position:50% align:center
You mean it’s better for him!

00:06:17.276 --> 00:06:18.861 line:90% position:50% align:center
For Max?

00:06:18.861 --> 00:06:20.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
What are you saying?

00:06:20.279 --> 00:06:21.488 line:90% position:50% align:center
What do you care?

00:06:21.488 --> 00:06:24.032 line:90% position:50% align:center
Don’t talk to me like that. Get back here!

00:06:54.563 --> 00:06:57.733 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, Olivia, what do you think
about the desk?

00:06:58.317 --> 00:07:00.528 line:90% position:50% align:center
Come here, sweetie. Come here.

00:07:09.537 --> 00:07:12.415 line:90% position:50% align:center
So you never forget that I love you.

00:07:13.249 --> 00:07:15.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
I hope you like it.

00:07:20.131 --> 00:07:25.052 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, every family
faces challenges of some sort.

00:07:25.052 --> 00:07:27.638 line:90% position:50% align:center
So let’s consult our road map together

00:07:27.638 --> 00:07:30.892 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the Bible at Romans 12:10.

00:07:30.892 --> 00:07:32.685 line:90% position:50% align:center
Would you read it with me, please?

00:07:32.685 --> 00:07:36.314 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s Romans 12:10:

00:07:36.314 --> 00:07:38.399 line:90% position:50% align:center
“In brotherly love

00:07:38.399 --> 00:07:42.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
“have tender affection for one another.

00:07:42.069 --> 00:07:46.657 line:90% position:50% align:center
In showing honor to one another,
take the lead.”

00:07:46.657 --> 00:07:48.910 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, what’s the point?

00:07:48.910 --> 00:07:51.913 line:90% position:50% align:center
Regardless of the role we play in the family,

00:07:51.913 --> 00:07:56.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
each of us needs to treat our family members
with love and respect.

00:07:56.668 --> 00:08:00.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
We need to “take the lead,”
or initiative, to do so.

00:08:00.755 --> 00:08:04.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
To help us, let’s consider four good habits

00:08:04.634 --> 00:08:07.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
that all of us should work
to develop more fully.

00:08:07.720 --> 00:08:09.764 line:90% position:50% align:center
Habit number one:

00:08:09.764 --> 00:08:13.601 line:90% position:50% align:center
Regularly express tender affection.

00:08:13.601 --> 00:08:15.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
When conveyed with sincerity,

00:08:15.854 --> 00:08:17.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
expressions of affection

00:08:17.856 --> 00:08:21.234 line:90% position:50% align:center
are like sunshine and water to plants.

00:08:21.234 --> 00:08:24.320 line:90% position:50% align:center
They help everyone
in the family grow and thrive.

00:08:25.280 --> 00:08:28.742 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the video we just watched,
did you note how Olivia

00:08:28.742 --> 00:08:33.538 line:90% position:50% align:center
cherished her father’s gift (that green desk)
and his tender words?

00:08:33.538 --> 00:08:38.376 line:90% position:50% align:center
He told her,
“So you never forget that I love you.”

00:08:38.376 --> 00:08:40.587 line:90% position:50% align:center
We also saw warm affection

00:08:40.587 --> 00:08:45.175 line:90% position:50% align:center
as the newly blended family
of Max and Irene looked at wedding photos.

00:08:45.175 --> 00:08:47.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
That was encouraging.

00:08:47.510 --> 00:08:50.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, here’s a question: How are we doing

00:08:50.430 --> 00:08:54.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
in expressing tender affection in our family?

00:08:54.100 --> 00:08:56.436 line:90% position:50% align:center
If that’s not one of our strengths,

00:08:56.436 --> 00:08:59.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
we might relate to a husband
who mustered up the courage

00:08:59.564 --> 00:09:02.025 line:90% position:50% align:center
to say “I love you” to his wife.

00:09:02.025 --> 00:09:05.070 line:90% position:50% align:center
It brought her to tears—tears of joy.

00:09:05.070 --> 00:09:08.824 line:90% position:50% align:center
And she said this, “I love you too,

00:09:08.824 --> 00:09:13.787 line:90% position:50% align:center
but this is the first time in 25 years
you’ve said it like that.”

00:09:13.787 --> 00:09:15.956 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, what’s the point?

00:09:15.956 --> 00:09:18.542 line:90% position:50% align:center
We don’t want to wait that long, of course,

00:09:18.542 --> 00:09:23.130 line:90% position:50% align:center
but even an awkward attempt
at expressing affection in our family

00:09:23.130 --> 00:09:27.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
is an act of love,
and it can do so much good.

00:09:27.634 --> 00:09:30.846 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s a habit we all want to cultivate.

00:09:30.846 --> 00:09:33.390 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s consider a second habit:

00:09:33.390 --> 00:09:35.851 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be kind in your actions,

00:09:35.851 --> 00:09:39.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
tone of voice, and choice of words.

00:09:39.021 --> 00:09:43.233 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the video, we recall Irene’s reassurance
to her daughter, Olivia.

00:09:43.233 --> 00:09:46.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
She said: “I know this is all new, baby.

00:09:46.403 --> 00:09:48.071 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be patient.”

00:09:48.071 --> 00:09:50.073 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mom was kind

00:09:50.073 --> 00:09:53.368 line:90% position:50% align:center
in what she said and how she said it.

00:09:53.368 --> 00:09:56.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
A little later, though, Olivia was upset.

00:09:56.246 --> 00:09:58.332 line:90% position:50% align:center
While we know she was hurt,

00:09:58.332 --> 00:10:02.336 line:90% position:50% align:center
her speech and actions were not so kind,
were they?

00:10:02.336 --> 00:10:04.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
During the pandemic,

00:10:04.296 --> 00:10:07.341 line:90% position:50% align:center
all of us have been under tremendous stress,

00:10:07.341 --> 00:10:10.177 line:90% position:50% align:center
and likely we didn’t always treat others

00:10:10.177 --> 00:10:13.180 line:90% position:50% align:center
in our family as kindly
as we would have liked.

00:10:13.180 --> 00:10:15.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, that’s in the past.

00:10:15.057 --> 00:10:17.893 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what can we all do now?

00:10:17.893 --> 00:10:21.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can pray to Jehovah
to help us “take the lead”

00:10:21.397 --> 00:10:23.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
in showing kindness.

00:10:23.691 --> 00:10:27.361 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example,
every day greeting one another kindly,

00:10:27.361 --> 00:10:30.114 line:90% position:50% align:center
every day saying “please” and “thank you,”

00:10:30.114 --> 00:10:34.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
sharing little gifts,
making time to talk, really listening

00:10:34.285 --> 00:10:37.747 line:90% position:50% align:center
—all of these are acts of kindness.

00:10:37.747 --> 00:10:40.916 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s a good habit we all want to cultivate.

00:10:41.959 --> 00:10:44.003 line:90% position:50% align:center
What’s habit number three?

00:10:44.003 --> 00:10:48.799 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be quick to apologize and forgive freely.

00:10:48.799 --> 00:10:52.011 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the video, Olivia’s new stepsister, Sue,

00:10:52.011 --> 00:10:56.390 line:90% position:50% align:center
apologized after she bumped into Olivia
with a box by mistake.

00:10:56.390 --> 00:10:59.810 line:90% position:50% align:center
That apology promoted peace.

00:10:59.810 --> 00:11:02.980 line:90% position:50% align:center
When you and I realize we’ve hurt someone

00:11:02.980 --> 00:11:05.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
even unintentionally, what should we do?

00:11:05.566 --> 00:11:08.402 line:90% position:50% align:center
We should make amends quickly.

00:11:08.402 --> 00:11:11.155 line:90% position:50% align:center
A mother named Marina said this:

00:11:11.155 --> 00:11:13.991 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We try to set a good example
for our children

00:11:13.991 --> 00:11:16.911 line:90% position:50% align:center
“in forgiving others
. . . and not getting offended.

00:11:16.911 --> 00:11:20.623 line:90% position:50% align:center
“When I am wrong, I apologize to my children.

00:11:20.623 --> 00:11:25.628 line:90% position:50% align:center
I want them to learn to do the same
in their dealings with others.”

00:11:25.628 --> 00:11:28.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s a good habit, wouldn’t you agree?

00:11:28.840 --> 00:11:31.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, let’s consider one more,
a fourth habit:

00:11:31.718 --> 00:11:36.264 line:90% position:50% align:center
Help your family members feel respected.

00:11:36.264 --> 00:11:40.810 line:90% position:50% align:center
An article in the <i>Awake!</i>  magazine
once made this insightful comment:

00:11:40.810 --> 00:11:45.315 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Respect is in the eye of the beholder.”

00:11:45.315 --> 00:11:47.358 line:90% position:50% align:center
What does that mean?

00:11:47.358 --> 00:11:50.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
Even if we think
we’re showing respect in the family,

00:11:50.487 --> 00:11:53.823 line:90% position:50% align:center
good questions to ask ourselves are:

00:11:53.823 --> 00:11:57.327 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Do my family members
feel that I respect them?

00:11:57.327 --> 00:12:01.164 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Is there more I can do to help my mate,
my children, or my parents

00:12:01.164 --> 00:12:03.958 line:90% position:50% align:center
feel loved and respected?’

00:12:05.335 --> 00:12:10.131 line:90% position:50% align:center
Brothers and sisters, when we fulfill
our God-given role in the family

00:12:10.131 --> 00:12:12.926 line:90% position:50% align:center
by developing good habits such as these,

00:12:12.926 --> 00:12:17.889 line:90% position:50% align:center
we show respect both for Jehovah
and for all of our family members.

00:12:17.889 --> 00:12:21.560 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, let’s think about Olivia and her mom.

00:12:21.560 --> 00:12:24.896 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the next video,
note how peace can be restored

00:12:24.896 --> 00:12:27.482 line:90% position:50% align:center
by showing love and respect.

00:12:38.452 --> 00:12:39.828 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s OK, Mom.

00:12:40.746 --> 00:12:41.913 line:90% position:50% align:center
You didn’t know.

00:12:41.913 --> 00:12:44.875 line:90% position:50% align:center
Dad did that for her just before he died.

00:12:48.462 --> 00:12:50.213 line:90% position:50% align:center
Anything I can do to help?

00:12:56.428 --> 00:12:58.889 line:90% position:50% align:center
Romans 12:10:

00:12:58.889 --> 00:13:03.518 line:90% position:50% align:center
“In showing honor to one another,
take the lead.”

00:13:11.193 --> 00:13:13.195 line:90% position:50% align:center
Olivia?

00:13:16.406 --> 00:13:18.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
I made your favorite tonight.

00:13:22.246 --> 00:13:23.706 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you.

00:13:30.963 --> 00:13:35.050 line:90% position:50% align:center
I wanted to tell you
that I didn’t handle that so well today.

00:13:35.759 --> 00:13:38.971 line:90% position:50% align:center
You had good reason
to be upset about the desk.

00:13:42.516 --> 00:13:45.936 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mom, you didn’t know.

00:13:47.688 --> 00:13:50.983 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s just one of those things
that Dad did just for me.

00:13:54.737 --> 00:13:56.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know he’s my stepdad now, but

00:13:57.907 --> 00:14:00.451 line:90% position:50% align:center
I just wish he would have checked first.

00:14:00.451 --> 00:14:02.244 line:90% position:50% align:center
It wasn’t Max.

00:14:02.244 --> 00:14:04.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was me.

00:14:04.955 --> 00:14:09.168 line:90% position:50% align:center
I wanted to surprise Max
with a place for him to do his work.

00:14:13.422 --> 00:14:16.342 line:90% position:50% align:center
So he didn’t make you get rid of the desk?

00:14:16.342 --> 00:14:17.885 line:90% position:50% align:center
No.

00:14:21.347 --> 00:14:24.350 line:90% position:50% align:center
I just thought you both didn’t care.

00:14:25.017 --> 00:14:29.939 line:90% position:50% align:center
I will never ever stop caring about you.

00:14:45.288 --> 00:14:47.874 line:90% position:50% align:center
What a beautiful outcome!

00:14:47.874 --> 00:14:52.295 line:90% position:50% align:center
The well-being and unity
of the family were restored.

00:14:52.295 --> 00:14:56.466 line:90% position:50% align:center
The mom, Irene,
applied the principle at Romans 12:10.

00:14:56.466 --> 00:15:01.387 line:90% position:50% align:center
She ‘took the lead,’ or the initiative,
to talk kindly with her daughter.

00:15:01.387 --> 00:15:05.350 line:90% position:50% align:center
Though Olivia was upset,
she too showed love and respect

00:15:05.350 --> 00:15:07.810 line:90% position:50% align:center
by being willing to listen to her mom.

00:15:07.810 --> 00:15:11.439 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a result,
the misunderstanding was cleared up,

00:15:11.439 --> 00:15:16.027 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Irene used the opportunity to reassure
her precious daughter of her love,

00:15:16.027 --> 00:15:20.990 line:90% position:50% align:center
saying, “I will never ever
stop caring about you.”

00:15:20.990 --> 00:15:23.451 line:90% position:50% align:center
And how our hearts were touched

00:15:23.451 --> 00:15:26.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
to see their warm embrace!

00:15:27.163 --> 00:15:31.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we “take the lead”
in applying Bible principles,

00:15:31.668 --> 00:15:34.879 line:90% position:50% align:center
we promote genuine family peace.

00:15:34.879 --> 00:15:37.799 line:90% position:50% align:center
So may all of us be determined

00:15:37.799 --> 00:15:42.596 line:90% position:50% align:center
to keep showing our family
that we truly love and respect them

00:15:42.596 --> 00:15:44.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
in word and action.

00:15:45.765 --> 00:15:48.643 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now please listen as Brother Robert Luccioni,

00:15:48.643 --> 00:15:52.022 line:90% position:50% align:center
a helper to the Publishing Committee,
considers the next talk

00:15:52.022 --> 00:15:54.649 line:90% position:50% align:center
of this symposium, with the theme 

00:15:54.649 --> 00:15:59.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Follow the Road Map to Family Peace
—Improve Communication.”

00:16:07.746 --> 00:16:09.748 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our previous talk reminded us

00:16:09.748 --> 00:16:13.335 line:90% position:50% align:center
that it’s possible
for a family to enjoy peace,

00:16:13.335 --> 00:16:15.337 line:90% position:50% align:center
but it takes work.

00:16:15.337 --> 00:16:20.050 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s look at one more step
that can help us stay on the road to peace,

00:16:20.050 --> 00:16:22.344 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that is good communication.

00:16:22.344 --> 00:16:26.974 line:90% position:50% align:center
A family promotes peace
when all the family members communicate

00:16:26.974 --> 00:16:30.519 line:90% position:50% align:center
in an open, calm, and honest manner.

00:16:30.519 --> 00:16:34.648 line:90% position:50% align:center
But how does communication help with peace?

00:16:34.648 --> 00:16:39.236 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, a pattern of good communication
keeps a family close.

00:16:39.236 --> 00:16:42.281 line:90% position:50% align:center
It helps us to identify and address problems

00:16:42.281 --> 00:16:46.034 line:90% position:50% align:center
before these reach a point
that they take peace away.

00:16:46.034 --> 00:16:48.245 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, that may seem obvious.

00:16:48.245 --> 00:16:52.499 line:90% position:50% align:center
But isn’t it true that we may find
that between work and school,

00:16:52.499 --> 00:16:57.171 line:90% position:50% align:center
the meetings and ministry,
and recreation and just life in general

00:16:57.171 --> 00:17:01.008 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s hard to find time
to communicate as a family?

00:17:01.008 --> 00:17:03.677 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is that a challenge in your family?

00:17:03.677 --> 00:17:06.180 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the following dramatization,

00:17:06.180 --> 00:17:10.476 line:90% position:50% align:center
notice what habits
hinder family communication.

00:17:19.068 --> 00:17:20.528 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, Steve.

00:17:22.738 --> 00:17:24.949 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, I’m sorry I was late to the meeting.

00:17:26.075 --> 00:17:28.911 line:90% position:50% align:center
I should have been there
to help out with my assignment.

00:17:30.579 --> 00:17:32.206 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, we got delayed.

00:17:36.502 --> 00:17:37.795 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re late!

00:17:37.795 --> 00:17:39.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s go, kids!

00:17:42.508 --> 00:17:44.760 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re coming! Sorry!

00:17:45.970 --> 00:17:48.472 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, the family is fine.

00:17:48.472 --> 00:17:51.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
Everybody is adjusting really well.

00:17:55.479 --> 00:17:57.523 line:90% position:50% align:center
Anyone seen my glasses?

00:18:00.193 --> 00:18:01.527 line:90% position:50% align:center
Anyone?

00:18:05.948 --> 00:18:07.950 line:90% position:50% align:center
I mean, we might be a little out of sync,

00:18:07.950 --> 00:18:11.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
but I don’t know

00:18:11.287 --> 00:18:13.664 line:90% position:50% align:center
—every family has their issues, right?

00:18:18.127 --> 00:18:19.837 line:90% position:50% align:center
You going outside in those?

00:18:21.965 --> 00:18:23.383 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mm-hmm.

00:18:24.759 --> 00:18:27.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, well, thanks for understanding.

00:18:27.971 --> 00:18:29.138 line:90% position:50% align:center
All right.

00:18:29.555 --> 00:18:30.890 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK. Take care.

00:18:30.890 --> 00:18:32.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
All right, bye-bye.

00:19:02.881 --> 00:19:06.968 line:90% position:50% align:center
Did you notice some habits
that hinder family communication?

00:19:06.968 --> 00:19:09.304 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the case of this family, it seems like

00:19:09.304 --> 00:19:12.390 line:90% position:50% align:center
technology is stifling their communication.

00:19:12.390 --> 00:19:15.936 line:90% position:50% align:center
And they obviously have some things
they need to communicate about

00:19:15.936 --> 00:19:20.315 line:90% position:50% align:center
—punctuality, dress and grooming—
but it’s not happening.

00:19:20.315 --> 00:19:22.317 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, while the scenes of them

00:19:22.317 --> 00:19:25.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
all looking at their devices
and ignoring one another

00:19:25.529 --> 00:19:27.989 line:90% position:50% align:center
may have been a bit humorous,

00:19:27.989 --> 00:19:31.493 line:90% position:50% align:center
did it remind you of your family at times?

00:19:31.493 --> 00:19:36.039 line:90% position:50% align:center
What a good reminder
for us not to let the use of technology

00:19:36.039 --> 00:19:40.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
rob our family of our time and attention!

00:19:40.127 --> 00:19:43.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
So how can we develop habits

00:19:43.255 --> 00:19:45.882 line:90% position:50% align:center
that promote good communication?

00:19:45.882 --> 00:19:50.137 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s consider the second Bible principle
of this symposium.

00:19:50.137 --> 00:19:53.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s turn together, please,
to Ephesians chapter 5.

00:19:53.432 --> 00:19:56.602 line:90% position:50% align:center
And let’s read verses 15 and 16

00:19:56.602 --> 00:19:59.605 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Ephesians 5:15, 16:

00:19:59.605 --> 00:20:02.024 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So keep strict watch that how you

00:20:02.024 --> 00:20:06.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
“walk is not as unwise but as wise persons,

00:20:06.111 --> 00:20:08.906 line:90% position:50% align:center
“making the best use of your time,

00:20:08.906 --> 00:20:11.200 line:90% position:50% align:center
because the days are wicked.”

00:20:11.200 --> 00:20:15.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, let’s look at two ways
that this Bible principle can help us.

00:20:15.287 --> 00:20:18.749 line:90% position:50% align:center
The first is by making time

00:20:18.749 --> 00:20:20.751 line:90% position:50% align:center
to have meaningful communication.

00:20:20.751 --> 00:20:23.253 line:90% position:50% align:center
Did you notice there in verse 16

00:20:23.253 --> 00:20:27.091 line:90% position:50% align:center
it says “making the best use of your time”?

00:20:27.091 --> 00:20:30.344 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, the study note for this phrase indicates

00:20:30.344 --> 00:20:33.847 line:90% position:50% align:center
the need to ‘buy out the time’
for important things

00:20:33.847 --> 00:20:35.849 line:90% position:50% align:center
from other pursuits.

00:20:35.849 --> 00:20:39.270 line:90% position:50% align:center
So how can this apply
to family communication?

00:20:39.270 --> 00:20:43.440 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, this could include
having a plan, or a routine,

00:20:43.440 --> 00:20:47.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
for when we spend time together
as a family each day.

00:20:47.611 --> 00:20:50.197 line:90% position:50% align:center
And during those times,
we may choose to limit

00:20:50.197 --> 00:20:54.744 line:90% position:50% align:center
our use of technology so that it
does not interfere with communication;

00:20:54.744 --> 00:20:59.415 line:90% position:50% align:center
perhaps it’s in the evening
or at a specific mealtime.

00:20:59.415 --> 00:21:02.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
One brother named Aaron stated,

00:21:02.668 --> 00:21:05.046 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We have our evening meal together,

00:21:05.046 --> 00:21:08.007 line:90% position:50% align:center
“which allows us time to talk
and hear what’s important

00:21:08.007 --> 00:21:10.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
to each member of the family.”

00:21:10.092 --> 00:21:13.054 line:90% position:50% align:center
He says: “My wife and I
have arranged our schedules

00:21:13.054 --> 00:21:15.765 line:90% position:50% align:center
“so we take the boys
to school and pick them up.

00:21:15.765 --> 00:21:18.601 line:90% position:50% align:center
This allows us to spend more time with them.”

00:21:18.601 --> 00:21:21.938 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then he says,
“My wife and I regularly take walks

00:21:21.938 --> 00:21:24.857 line:90% position:50% align:center
and freely talk about our concerns.”

00:21:24.857 --> 00:21:26.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
What’s the point?

00:21:26.859 --> 00:21:29.737 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, they’re making good use of their time.

00:21:29.737 --> 00:21:33.991 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, to do this, they’ve had to buy
that time out from other pursuits.

00:21:33.991 --> 00:21:37.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
But they have a plan; they have a routine.

00:21:37.161 --> 00:21:40.832 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what plan, or routine,

00:21:40.832 --> 00:21:45.461 line:90% position:50% align:center
does your family have
for meaningful communication each day?

00:21:46.170 --> 00:21:49.799 line:90% position:50% align:center
If you don’t have one, can you start now?

00:21:49.799 --> 00:21:54.137 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s look at the second way
that this Bible principle can help us.

00:21:54.137 --> 00:21:57.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that is by determining when and how

00:21:57.682 --> 00:22:00.768 line:90% position:50% align:center
to deal with problems when they do arise.

00:22:00.768 --> 00:22:04.480 line:90% position:50% align:center
You notice verse 15 in Ephesians chapter 5

00:22:04.480 --> 00:22:08.151 line:90% position:50% align:center
says that we should ‘walk as wise persons.’

00:22:08.151 --> 00:22:11.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
It means we need
to choose our paths carefully,

00:22:11.112 --> 00:22:16.117 line:90% position:50% align:center
knowing when to go, when to stop,
when to take another route.

00:22:16.117 --> 00:22:19.746 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, how can that help us
when problems arise?

00:22:19.746 --> 00:22:21.956 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, a wise person

00:22:21.956 --> 00:22:25.585 line:90% position:50% align:center
generally knows when is and when is not

00:22:25.585 --> 00:22:27.962 line:90% position:50% align:center
a good time to address a problem.

00:22:27.962 --> 00:22:32.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example, we all can attest
that when emotions are high,

00:22:32.634 --> 00:22:36.930 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s probably not the best time
to bring up an issue.

00:22:36.930 --> 00:22:39.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
One father states:

00:22:39.140 --> 00:22:42.352 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Sometimes we need to wait
and let things cool.

00:22:42.352 --> 00:22:45.647 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Often a night’s rest
with prayer makes a big difference

00:22:45.647 --> 00:22:49.109 line:90% position:50% align:center
when we address the issue the next morning.”

00:22:49.109 --> 00:22:51.444 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s a wise person.

00:22:51.444 --> 00:22:54.906 line:90% position:50% align:center
A wise person also listens.

00:22:54.906 --> 00:22:58.952 line:90% position:50% align:center
James 1:19 reminds us to “be quick to listen,

00:22:58.952 --> 00:23:02.080 line:90% position:50% align:center
slow to speak, [and] slow to anger.”

00:23:02.080 --> 00:23:04.124 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thus, we can go to Jehovah in prayer

00:23:04.124 --> 00:23:07.085 line:90% position:50% align:center
and ask him to help us to really listen,

00:23:07.085 --> 00:23:10.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
to stay calm, to stay humble.

00:23:10.505 --> 00:23:13.842 line:90% position:50% align:center
One sister named Dawn states,

00:23:13.842 --> 00:23:16.803 line:90% position:50% align:center
“When there are problems,
the first thing I do

00:23:16.803 --> 00:23:21.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
is ask Jehovah in prayer to help us
resolve the problem calmly.”

00:23:21.308 --> 00:23:25.270 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then she says, “Then we talk
with the family member privately

00:23:25.270 --> 00:23:29.733 line:90% position:50% align:center
and really try to listen
to their side of the issue.”

00:23:29.733 --> 00:23:32.027 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s a wise person.

00:23:32.027 --> 00:23:35.197 line:90% position:50% align:center
A wise person will also consider the approach

00:23:35.197 --> 00:23:38.659 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the words that he or she uses.

00:23:38.659 --> 00:23:42.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example, rather than telling
our family member that they have a problem,

00:23:42.121 --> 00:23:46.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
can we turn it around so that it’s something
that we all need to work on together?

00:23:46.583 --> 00:23:49.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you reassure your family members

00:23:49.378 --> 00:23:53.173 line:90% position:50% align:center
that you really love them
and you want to understand

00:23:53.173 --> 00:23:55.926 line:90% position:50% align:center
their side of the issue or the problem?

00:23:55.926 --> 00:23:59.555 line:90% position:50% align:center
See, now, doing this,
we’re not attacking the family member

00:23:59.555 --> 00:24:03.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
but, rather,
showing that we’re all in this together.

00:24:03.100 --> 00:24:06.562 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we see benefits of this Bible principle

00:24:06.562 --> 00:24:09.315 line:90% position:50% align:center
in communication in our family, don’t we?

00:24:09.315 --> 00:24:13.861 line:90% position:50% align:center
You notice the two points:
(1) making the best use of our time

00:24:13.861 --> 00:24:18.699 line:90% position:50% align:center
and (2) walking as wise persons.

00:24:18.699 --> 00:24:23.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, communication will always be
a work in progress,

00:24:23.287 --> 00:24:26.457 line:90% position:50% align:center
but it’s worth the effort,
as it will go a long way

00:24:26.457 --> 00:24:29.043 line:90% position:50% align:center
to bringing peace to your family.

00:24:29.043 --> 00:24:31.754 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s watch more of our dramatization

00:24:31.754 --> 00:24:34.882 line:90% position:50% align:center
and notice the benefits of developing habits

00:24:34.882 --> 00:24:37.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
that promote good communication.

00:24:41.305 --> 00:24:43.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
I don’t know.

00:24:43.391 --> 00:24:45.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
What do you think?

00:24:45.101 --> 00:24:48.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
We all have to work on it.
I know I need to.

00:24:48.855 --> 00:24:51.107 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why don’t we approach it that way
with the kids

00:24:51.107 --> 00:24:53.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
—just be open with them?

00:24:53.192 --> 00:24:55.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
That sounds like a good idea.

00:24:56.571 --> 00:25:01.159 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK. So Irene and I have been talking about

00:25:01.159 --> 00:25:03.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
communication

00:25:03.161 --> 00:25:05.163 line:90% position:50% align:center
in our family.

00:25:05.788 --> 00:25:08.374 line:90% position:50% align:center
We wanted to talk
about our phones and other devices.

00:25:09.500 --> 00:25:11.044 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re not talking about me, are you?

00:25:11.044 --> 00:25:11.669 line:90% position:50% align:center
You can’t do that.

00:25:11.669 --> 00:25:12.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
No, no.

00:25:12.086 --> 00:25:13.504 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know that we can all be
more balanced, but . . .

00:25:13.504 --> 00:25:14.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
I need it.

00:25:14.505 --> 00:25:16.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re joking, right? You mean them.

00:25:16.049 --> 00:25:16.841 line:90% position:50% align:center
You can’t take them away.

00:25:16.841 --> 00:25:17.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
I haven’t done anything bad.

00:25:17.967 --> 00:25:19.093 line:90% position:50% align:center
I have responsibilities.

00:25:19.093 --> 00:25:19.636 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hold on.

00:25:19.636 --> 00:25:20.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re always on your phone too.

00:25:20.678 --> 00:25:21.387 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s true.

00:25:21.387 --> 00:25:22.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s OK.

00:25:22.764 --> 00:25:25.558 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s just talk about it, all right?

00:25:27.352 --> 00:25:28.102 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sue,

00:25:29.562 --> 00:25:33.775 line:90% position:50% align:center
can you read Ephesians 5:15, 16
for us, please?

00:25:36.903 --> 00:25:39.405 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So keep strict watch that how you walk

00:25:39.405 --> 00:25:43.618 line:90% position:50% align:center
“is not as unwise but as wise persons,

00:25:43.618 --> 00:25:48.039 line:90% position:50% align:center
making the best use of your time,
because the days are wicked.”

00:25:49.708 --> 00:25:50.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
So

00:25:51.501 --> 00:25:55.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
how do you think we’re doing
with our phones and other devices?

00:26:02.470 --> 00:26:05.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
It isn’t that what you’re doing
on your devices is wrong.

00:26:05.932 --> 00:26:07.726 line:90% position:50% align:center
Exactly.

00:26:07.726 --> 00:26:10.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
But could it be taking time away
from more important things

00:26:12.230 --> 00:26:14.399 line:90% position:50% align:center
—like talking to each other,

00:26:16.026 --> 00:26:19.738 line:90% position:50% align:center
and in that way affecting even
how we’re talking to each other?

00:26:25.744 --> 00:26:29.790 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, I think it’d be smart

00:26:29.790 --> 00:26:31.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
to have some boundaries then.

00:26:36.713 --> 00:26:38.423 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, OK.

00:26:40.884 --> 00:26:42.219 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.

00:26:43.345 --> 00:26:44.721 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.

00:26:44.721 --> 00:26:46.723 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s talk about how we can do that.

00:26:50.769 --> 00:26:51.979 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey!

00:26:51.979 --> 00:26:53.230 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, Olivia.

00:26:53.230 --> 00:26:54.064 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey.

00:26:56.358 --> 00:26:59.820 line:90% position:50% align:center
Evidently, I haven’t figured out
how to talk to her about her clothes yet.

00:26:59.820 --> 00:27:00.362 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hmm.

00:27:00.362 --> 00:27:02.114 line:90% position:50% align:center
I need your help.

00:27:02.114 --> 00:27:04.116 line:90% position:50% align:center
I got this one.

00:27:07.828 --> 00:27:09.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know,

00:27:09.955 --> 00:27:13.083 line:90% position:50% align:center
but it’s all about good spiritual judgment.

00:27:13.083 --> 00:27:17.921 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you think that these trends reflect
Jehovah’s view of “respectable dress”?

00:27:20.466 --> 00:27:22.593 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know that you’ll do the right thing.

00:27:25.804 --> 00:27:26.597 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.

00:27:27.306 --> 00:27:28.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, Gabe, can you take us?

00:27:28.682 --> 00:27:29.725 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, of course.

00:27:29.725 --> 00:27:30.684 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mm-hmm.

00:27:30.976 --> 00:27:33.604 line:90% position:50% align:center
While we’re all here,

00:27:33.604 --> 00:27:36.732 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know we all have
different views on punctuality,

00:27:37.900 --> 00:27:39.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
but

00:27:39.068 --> 00:27:40.778 line:90% position:50% align:center
I really need your help

00:27:40.778 --> 00:27:43.781 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that I can take care
of some of my responsibilities.

00:27:44.907 --> 00:27:46.951 line:90% position:50% align:center
You think we can meet in the middle?

00:27:48.285 --> 00:27:48.786 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.

00:27:48.786 --> 00:27:49.286 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:27:49.286 --> 00:27:51.288 line:90% position:50% align:center
All right. Great.

00:28:11.767 --> 00:28:14.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, this symposium has been discussing

00:28:14.395 --> 00:28:18.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
four Bible principles
that can guide families to peace.

00:28:18.316 --> 00:28:21.027 line:90% position:50% align:center
Brother Dellinger considered the first one

00:28:21.027 --> 00:28:23.362 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Romans 12:10.

00:28:23.362 --> 00:28:27.366 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in this part, we considered
Ephesians chapter 5,

00:28:27.366 --> 00:28:29.577 line:90% position:50% align:center
verses 15, 16.

00:28:29.577 --> 00:28:33.915 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, did we see how this scripture
helped our family in the video?

00:28:33.915 --> 00:28:37.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we saw that they knew down deep
that they were not making

00:28:37.377 --> 00:28:40.963 line:90% position:50% align:center
the best use of their time,
so they made changes.

00:28:40.963 --> 00:28:44.133 line:90% position:50% align:center
They saw that they needed to set boundaries

00:28:44.133 --> 00:28:46.886 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that they could improve
their communication.

00:28:46.886 --> 00:28:50.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
We also saw how the family
—the parents—acted as wise persons.

00:28:50.932 --> 00:28:51.975 line:90% position:50% align:center
How?

00:28:51.975 --> 00:28:54.686 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, by determining when and how

00:28:54.686 --> 00:28:57.438 line:90% position:50% align:center
to address the problems
that needed to be addressed,

00:28:57.438 --> 00:29:01.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
such as the use of technology,
dress and grooming,

00:29:01.526 --> 00:29:03.862 line:90% position:50% align:center
and punctuality.

00:29:03.862 --> 00:29:07.031 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, can this Bible principle
help your family

00:29:07.031 --> 00:29:10.326 line:90% position:50% align:center
—help my family—to improve communication?

00:29:10.326 --> 00:29:12.871 line:90% position:50% align:center
Would this be a good scripture to include

00:29:12.871 --> 00:29:15.915 line:90% position:50% align:center
in your next family worship?

00:29:15.915 --> 00:29:20.587 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, it takes time to learn how
to communicate well as a family.

00:29:20.587 --> 00:29:23.048 line:90% position:50% align:center
But it is worth the effort.

00:29:23.048 --> 00:29:24.466 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

00:29:24.466 --> 00:29:28.136 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, if we strive to communicate
well each day,

00:29:28.136 --> 00:29:31.640 line:90% position:50% align:center
then communication will come more readily

00:29:31.640 --> 00:29:33.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
when there are problems.

00:29:33.642 --> 00:29:36.603 line:90% position:50% align:center
So be determined to look for ways

00:29:36.603 --> 00:29:39.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
to improve communication in your family.

00:29:39.773 --> 00:29:42.984 line:90% position:50% align:center
And by taking this initiative
and sticking with it,

00:29:42.984 --> 00:29:45.570 line:90% position:50% align:center
you will be following the road map

00:29:45.570 --> 00:29:47.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
to family peace.

00:29:48.281 --> 00:29:52.619 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please listen now to Brother David Splane,
a member of the Governing Body,

00:29:52.619 --> 00:29:56.039 line:90% position:50% align:center
as he considers the next talk
of this symposium,

00:29:56.039 --> 00:30:00.460 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Follow the Road Map to Family Peace
—Work as a Team.”

00:30:08.635 --> 00:30:12.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah intended married couples
to work together.

00:30:12.431 --> 00:30:15.183 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s why Jesus used the expression we find

00:30:15.183 --> 00:30:18.103 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Matthew 19:6.

00:30:18.103 --> 00:30:23.025 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s read this from the Bible
—Matthew 19.

00:30:23.025 --> 00:30:25.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I’ll give you a moment.

00:30:26.111 --> 00:30:30.991 line:90% position:50% align:center
Matthew chapter 19
—now, we’re going to read verse 6.

00:30:32.534 --> 00:30:35.079 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, first of all, Jesus quotes

00:30:35.079 --> 00:30:37.831 line:90% position:50% align:center
from Genesis 2:24.

00:30:37.831 --> 00:30:40.417 line:90% position:50% align:center
Speaking of married couples, he says:

00:30:40.417 --> 00:30:44.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So that they are no longer two,
but one flesh.”

00:30:44.296 --> 00:30:49.051 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, you remember, Jehovah
made that comment in the garden of Eden.

00:30:49.051 --> 00:30:53.264 line:90% position:50% align:center
But now Jesus adds something
that isn’t in Genesis.

00:30:53.264 --> 00:30:58.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
He says: “Therefore, what God has yoked

00:30:58.227 --> 00:31:01.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
“[yoked] together,

00:31:01.021 --> 00:31:03.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
let no man put apart.”

00:31:04.608 --> 00:31:08.612 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we think of a yoke,
we may think of a team of horses

00:31:08.612 --> 00:31:11.699 line:90% position:50% align:center
plowing a field or pulling a heavy wagon.

00:31:11.699 --> 00:31:15.786 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, if they pull together,
they can be a powerful force.

00:31:15.786 --> 00:31:19.498 line:90% position:50% align:center
The same is true
when family members work together.

00:31:21.250 --> 00:31:24.045 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mom, Dad

00:31:25.046 --> 00:31:28.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
—you have excellent reasons to work together.

00:31:28.924 --> 00:31:32.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
When you work together,
you contribute to the peace of the family.

00:31:32.720 --> 00:31:36.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
And think of the effect
it has on the children.

00:31:36.182 --> 00:31:40.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
By working together, you’re teaching
that fine young son of yours

00:31:40.186 --> 00:31:42.438 line:90% position:50% align:center
how to be a caring husband and father,

00:31:42.438 --> 00:31:47.109 line:90% position:50% align:center
and your beautiful daughter how to be
a supportive wife and mother.

00:31:48.361 --> 00:31:52.281 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what happens when teammates
begin pulling in opposite directions

00:31:52.281 --> 00:31:54.742 line:90% position:50% align:center
or when one puts on the brakes?

00:31:54.742 --> 00:31:56.786 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s watch a video.

00:31:56.786 --> 00:31:58.830 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, here’s the setup.

00:31:58.830 --> 00:32:03.000 line:90% position:50% align:center
For a long time, a sister raised
her two children as a single parent,

00:32:03.000 --> 00:32:05.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
and she did a great job of it.

00:32:05.378 --> 00:32:09.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then she married a very kind brother.

00:32:09.215 --> 00:32:11.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
The family has a new head.

00:32:11.217 --> 00:32:15.054 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s see how well the sister
is adapting to her new role.

00:32:19.267 --> 00:32:23.521 line:90% position:50% align:center
The last few weeks of family worship
have been nice,

00:32:23.521 --> 00:32:25.273 line:90% position:50% align:center
right?

00:32:25.273 --> 00:32:26.858 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:32:26.858 --> 00:32:30.653 line:90% position:50% align:center
All these things we ask and pray
in Jesus’ name, Amen.

00:32:30.653 --> 00:32:31.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
Amen.

00:32:35.617 --> 00:32:36.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK, this week . . .

00:32:36.576 --> 00:32:39.079 line:90% position:50% align:center
We are in chapter 5.

00:32:39.079 --> 00:32:40.663 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yep, that’s right.

00:32:40.663 --> 00:32:42.916 line:90% position:50% align:center
And last week, Gabe read, so this week . . .

00:32:42.916 --> 00:32:44.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s Sue’s turn.

00:32:45.085 --> 00:32:47.504 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s right.
It’s Sue’s turn.

00:32:48.922 --> 00:32:50.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK, the point here is
that when it comes . . .

00:32:50.924 --> 00:32:54.469 line:90% position:50% align:center
Honey, maybe an illustration would be better.

00:32:55.595 --> 00:32:58.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
Um, OK.

00:32:59.766 --> 00:33:01.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s like a bird . . .

00:33:02.060 --> 00:33:04.229 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, hopefully I was able to clear that up
for you a little bit, Olivia.

00:33:04.229 --> 00:33:06.022 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah. Thank you.

00:33:06.022 --> 00:33:08.692 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, actually, Max, that’s not true.

00:33:08.692 --> 00:33:11.236 line:90% position:50% align:center
We had an updated understanding
in the recent <i>Watchtower.</i>

00:33:13.864 --> 00:33:15.240 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thanks.

00:33:19.453 --> 00:33:23.874 line:90% position:50% align:center
I think they went really well, right?

00:33:25.333 --> 00:33:27.711 line:90% position:50% align:center
Um, actually . . .

00:33:31.214 --> 00:33:32.299 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey.

00:33:34.801 --> 00:33:36.803 line:90% position:50% align:center
Maybe we can talk about it later.

00:33:38.347 --> 00:33:39.473 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.

00:33:53.862 --> 00:33:56.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
The sister isn’t a bad person.

00:33:56.406 --> 00:33:59.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we can ask:
What is she teaching her daughter

00:33:59.284 --> 00:34:01.537 line:90% position:50% align:center
about the wife’s role in the family?

00:34:01.537 --> 00:34:04.039 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what is her son learning
about taking the lead

00:34:04.039 --> 00:34:06.083 line:90% position:50% align:center
as the man of the house?

00:34:06.083 --> 00:34:09.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
He hasn’t had a man
in his life for a long time.

00:34:09.378 --> 00:34:11.422 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now there is one.

00:34:11.422 --> 00:34:14.341 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s safe to say that the kids
will stand a better chance

00:34:14.341 --> 00:34:16.802 line:90% position:50% align:center
of having a successful marriage themselves

00:34:16.802 --> 00:34:20.389 line:90% position:50% align:center
when they see their parents pulling together.

00:34:20.389 --> 00:34:24.518 line:90% position:50% align:center
A little later, we’ll see how
the husband handles the situation,

00:34:24.518 --> 00:34:27.271 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we brothers
are going to want to pay attention.

00:34:27.271 --> 00:34:29.398 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is a classic.

00:34:31.442 --> 00:34:34.987 line:90% position:50% align:center
Family life is more pleasant when Dad, Mom,

00:34:34.987 --> 00:34:38.032 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the kids work together as a team.

00:34:38.032 --> 00:34:40.201 line:90% position:50% align:center
The family head is the captain.

00:34:40.201 --> 00:34:42.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
He needs to make sure that everyone knows

00:34:42.328 --> 00:34:44.663 line:90% position:50% align:center
what goals the family is working toward

00:34:44.663 --> 00:34:49.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
and how each one can contribute
toward achieving those goals.

00:34:49.251 --> 00:34:52.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
When it’s your family’s turn
to help clean the Kingdom Hall

00:34:52.296 --> 00:34:54.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
or a convention venue, for example,

00:34:54.924 --> 00:34:56.968 line:90% position:50% align:center
don’t leave the kids at home.

00:34:56.968 --> 00:34:58.594 line:90% position:50% align:center
They’re part of the team.

00:34:58.594 --> 00:35:00.846 line:90% position:50% align:center
Don’t go there with half the team.

00:35:00.846 --> 00:35:05.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let them experience the joy
that comes from serving others.

00:35:05.101 --> 00:35:07.520 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let them work along with you.

00:35:07.520 --> 00:35:09.730 line:90% position:50% align:center
If you’re assigned to clean the restrooms,

00:35:09.730 --> 00:35:12.817 line:90% position:50% align:center
don’t complain about it—a very fine example.

00:35:12.817 --> 00:35:17.196 line:90% position:50% align:center
Your children will learn that when
there’s work to be done, we just do it.

00:35:17.196 --> 00:35:22.118 line:90% position:50% align:center
We aren’t picky about what we will
and will not do.

00:35:22.118 --> 00:35:25.663 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we don’t feel
that some jobs are beneath us.

00:35:25.663 --> 00:35:27.999 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, this is in line with Paul’s counsel

00:35:27.999 --> 00:35:32.045 line:90% position:50% align:center
found at Philippians 2:3, 4.

00:35:33.254 --> 00:35:35.465 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s look that up.

00:35:35.465 --> 00:35:37.759 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s good exercise

00:35:37.759 --> 00:35:40.470 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Philippians chapter 2,

00:35:40.470 --> 00:35:43.473 line:90% position:50% align:center
verses 3, 4.

00:35:44.849 --> 00:35:48.102 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, we’re thinking about the family
as a team here.

00:35:48.102 --> 00:35:52.065 line:90% position:50% align:center
It says: “Do nothing out of contentiousness

00:35:52.065 --> 00:35:54.484 line:90% position:50% align:center
“or out of egotism,

00:35:54.484 --> 00:35:59.405 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but with humility consider
others superior to you,

00:35:59.405 --> 00:36:03.243 line:90% position:50% align:center
“as you look out
not only for your own interests,

00:36:03.243 --> 00:36:06.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
but also for the interests of others.”

00:36:07.205 --> 00:36:10.417 line:90% position:50% align:center
When there’s work to be done,
someone has to do it.

00:36:10.417 --> 00:36:15.213 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do I think that I’m so special
that someone else has to look after it?

00:36:16.506 --> 00:36:19.968 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some families volunteer
to help with Kingdom Hall maintenance.

00:36:19.968 --> 00:36:22.637 line:90% position:50% align:center
When the kids are old enough,
they can work on other projects

00:36:22.637 --> 00:36:24.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
like working on an Assembly Hall.

00:36:24.598 --> 00:36:26.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
They have a ball!

00:36:26.349 --> 00:36:29.519 line:90% position:50% align:center
The friendships that you
and your young people will forge

00:36:29.519 --> 00:36:31.646 line:90% position:50% align:center
can last a lifetime.

00:36:31.646 --> 00:36:33.982 line:90% position:50% align:center
And here’s a bonus: When the young people

00:36:33.982 --> 00:36:36.776 line:90% position:50% align:center
go to a circuit assembly
or a regional convention,

00:36:36.776 --> 00:36:39.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
they’ll have good friends to associate with

00:36:39.529 --> 00:36:44.117 line:90% position:50% align:center
—both young and old—
people they’ve been working with.

00:36:46.161 --> 00:36:49.373 line:90% position:50% align:center
What about working around the house?

00:36:49.373 --> 00:36:53.126 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some parents feel that the children
shouldn’t have to help out at all

00:36:53.126 --> 00:36:56.046 line:90% position:50% align:center
because they have their schoolwork to do.

00:36:56.046 --> 00:36:58.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
But their schoolwork is something
they do for themselves.

00:36:58.924 --> 00:37:02.427 line:90% position:50% align:center
How are they contributing
to the welfare of the family?

00:37:02.427 --> 00:37:06.306 line:90% position:50% align:center
How are they learning
to serve others unselfishly?

00:37:06.306 --> 00:37:11.061 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s good for a child to feel that he has
an important role in the household

00:37:11.061 --> 00:37:13.313 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that people are counting on him.

00:37:13.313 --> 00:37:17.067 line:90% position:50% align:center
Think what that does for his self-respect.

00:37:17.067 --> 00:37:19.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
A father named Steven said,

00:37:19.611 --> 00:37:22.072 line:90% position:50% align:center
“When nothing is expected of them,

00:37:22.072 --> 00:37:24.825 line:90% position:50% align:center
“children learn that they
are here to be served,

00:37:24.825 --> 00:37:27.494 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and they grow up with a distorted view

00:37:27.494 --> 00:37:30.456 line:90% position:50% align:center
of what life will require of them.”

00:37:31.665 --> 00:37:34.126 line:90% position:50% align:center
We might ask, Would a young person

00:37:34.126 --> 00:37:36.920 line:90% position:50% align:center
with that attitude
even be able to keep a job?

00:37:38.213 --> 00:37:40.633 line:90% position:50% align:center
When some in the world lose their job,

00:37:40.633 --> 00:37:43.469 line:90% position:50% align:center
they remain unemployed for a long time.

00:37:43.469 --> 00:37:45.262 line:90% position:50% align:center
They can’t pay the bills.

00:37:45.262 --> 00:37:48.849 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yet, there are job opportunities
all around them,

00:37:48.849 --> 00:37:52.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
but they consider those jobs beneath them.

00:37:52.186 --> 00:37:56.565 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what’s one of the most annoying traits
an employee can have?

00:37:56.565 --> 00:37:58.567 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ask any boss.

00:37:58.567 --> 00:38:01.570 line:90% position:50% align:center
When the worker is asked to do something,
he replies,

00:38:01.570 --> 00:38:03.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
“That’s not my job.”

00:38:04.490 --> 00:38:08.244 line:90% position:50% align:center
Teach your child that anything
that needs to be done

00:38:08.244 --> 00:38:12.707 line:90% position:50% align:center
is his job if he’s old enough
and capable of doing it.

00:38:14.291 --> 00:38:18.504 line:90% position:50% align:center
How early should parents
start to assign chores to their children?

00:38:18.504 --> 00:38:21.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some experts have found that children who are

00:38:21.924 --> 00:38:24.802 line:90% position:50% align:center
three years old or even younger

00:38:24.802 --> 00:38:27.388 line:90% position:50% align:center
can be taught to help out.

00:38:27.388 --> 00:38:32.018 line:90% position:50% align:center
They can learn to pick up their toys,
clean up spills, sort laundry.

00:38:32.018 --> 00:38:34.312 line:90% position:50% align:center
Older children can vacuum,

00:38:34.312 --> 00:38:37.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
wash the car, prepare a meal.

00:38:37.106 --> 00:38:40.109 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m happy to say that many young brothers
here at Bethel

00:38:40.109 --> 00:38:43.946 line:90% position:50% align:center
are excellent cooks,
which is often the result

00:38:43.946 --> 00:38:47.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
of fine parental training.

00:38:47.033 --> 00:38:49.410 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you remember the video where Caleb

00:38:49.410 --> 00:38:52.205 line:90% position:50% align:center
is taught to clean his room
and put away his toys?

00:38:52.205 --> 00:38:55.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
That video was a game changer
for many children.

00:38:55.833 --> 00:38:58.711 line:90% position:50% align:center
They want to be just like Caleb.

00:38:58.711 --> 00:39:03.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
And now when you enter their room,
you can find the bed.

00:39:04.968 --> 00:39:09.764 line:90% position:50% align:center
When problems arise,
attack the problem, not each other.

00:39:09.764 --> 00:39:14.018 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s not ‘How can I win?’
but ‘How can we win?’

00:39:14.018 --> 00:39:18.398 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’ll see an excellent example of that
in the follow-up video.

00:39:18.398 --> 00:39:19.816 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s watch.

00:39:31.494 --> 00:39:32.996 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey!

00:39:32.996 --> 00:39:34.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
Want some tea?

00:39:34.622 --> 00:39:35.999 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sure!

00:39:42.964 --> 00:39:44.341 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, babe,

00:39:44.341 --> 00:39:47.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
you and me, we’re a team, right?

00:39:47.135 --> 00:39:48.637 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, of course!

00:39:50.263 --> 00:39:53.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
When I read this, I thought about us.

00:39:56.728 --> 00:40:01.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So that they are no longer two,
but one flesh.”

00:40:03.235 --> 00:40:07.989 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know that before, you had to shoulder
everything yourself for so long.

00:40:07.989 --> 00:40:08.740 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mm-hmm.

00:40:08.740 --> 00:40:10.242 line:90% position:50% align:center
And you did great.

00:40:10.242 --> 00:40:15.163 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’ve been raising two beautiful,
spiritual kids on your own.

00:40:16.957 --> 00:40:18.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
But now you have me.

00:40:18.834 --> 00:40:20.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, I do.

00:40:21.336 --> 00:40:24.673 line:90% position:50% align:center
So do you think
sometimes we’re not a team?

00:40:24.673 --> 00:40:26.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, it’s just that sometimes
during family worship . . .

00:40:26.925 --> 00:40:30.012 line:90% position:50% align:center
I get excited, and I jump in. I know!

00:40:30.804 --> 00:40:33.891 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m just so used to doing it
after all these years.

00:40:33.891 --> 00:40:36.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know you’re not trying to take over.

00:40:36.101 --> 00:40:38.604 line:90% position:50% align:center
And listen, I love the way you teach.

00:40:38.604 --> 00:40:40.606 line:90% position:50% align:center
I see how you can reach the kids

00:40:40.606 --> 00:40:42.608 line:90% position:50% align:center
in ways that I can’t.

00:40:43.567 --> 00:40:47.154 line:90% position:50% align:center
Just let me guide it,
and I’ll make sure you can do that.

00:40:48.238 --> 00:40:51.366 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thanks, honey. Thanks for your patience.

00:40:51.366 --> 00:40:53.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
No, thank you for your patience.

00:40:53.702 --> 00:40:57.790 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m a work in progress,
but we make a great team.

00:40:59.625 --> 00:41:03.629 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why don’t we look at what we’re going
to cover before our next family worship?

00:41:03.629 --> 00:41:05.839 line:90% position:50% align:center
That sounds great.

00:41:10.678 --> 00:41:12.846 line:90% position:50% align:center
Wasn’t that a fine example

00:41:12.846 --> 00:41:16.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
of how to attack a problem and not your mate?

00:41:16.100 --> 00:41:19.687 line:90% position:50% align:center
No arguments, no raised voices,

00:41:19.687 --> 00:41:24.525 line:90% position:50% align:center
no accusations
—the husband had empathy for his wife.

00:41:24.525 --> 00:41:26.527 line:90% position:50% align:center
He didn’t question her motives.

00:41:26.527 --> 00:41:28.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
He realized that as a single parent,

00:41:28.487 --> 00:41:31.949 line:90% position:50% align:center
she’d been taking the lead for a long time.

00:41:31.949 --> 00:41:36.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
And notice how she responded
to her husband’s kind counsel.

00:41:36.287 --> 00:41:40.916 line:90% position:50% align:center
No doubt it’s going to be easy
for the kids to respect their stepfather,

00:41:40.916 --> 00:41:44.003 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they’re going to learn
how a husband and wife

00:41:44.003 --> 00:41:47.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
should treat each other
and how they should pull together.

00:41:49.008 --> 00:41:53.429 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sometime soon, you might want
to consider these questions:

00:41:53.429 --> 00:41:58.059 line:90% position:50% align:center
In what aspects of our marriage
do we work well as a team?

00:41:58.059 --> 00:42:02.104 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then, how can we improve?

00:42:02.104 --> 00:42:04.315 line:90% position:50% align:center
It pleases Jehovah

00:42:04.315 --> 00:42:07.401 line:90% position:50% align:center
when family members work together as a team.

00:42:07.401 --> 00:42:09.904 line:90% position:50% align:center
That promotes peace in the family.

00:42:09.904 --> 00:42:14.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
And our God is a “God of peace.”

00:42:15.743 --> 00:42:18.538 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now Brother John Ekrann

00:42:18.538 --> 00:42:21.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
will consider the final talk
of this symposium,

00:42:21.416 --> 00:42:24.669 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Follow the Road Map to Family Peace

00:42:24.669 --> 00:42:27.839 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Worship Jehovah Together.”

00:42:35.763 --> 00:42:39.434 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah wants your family
to be happy and peaceful.

00:42:39.434 --> 00:42:41.436 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Jehovah does more than simply say,

00:42:41.436 --> 00:42:44.063 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I hope you have a peaceful family life.”

00:42:44.063 --> 00:42:48.401 line:90% position:50% align:center
He explains exactly how we
can get our family there.

00:42:48.401 --> 00:42:51.571 line:90% position:50% align:center
I want you to imagine Jehovah
laying out a map in front of you

00:42:51.571 --> 00:42:53.823 line:90% position:50% align:center
and saying: “See these landmarks?

00:42:53.823 --> 00:42:56.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Look for them on the road to peace.

00:42:56.284 --> 00:42:59.329 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if you see them,
you’re going in the right direction.”

00:43:00.455 --> 00:43:02.624 line:90% position:50% align:center
So far in this symposium, we’ve passed

00:43:02.624 --> 00:43:05.460 line:90% position:50% align:center
the landmarks of showing love and respect,

00:43:05.460 --> 00:43:07.462 line:90% position:50% align:center
improving communication,

00:43:07.462 --> 00:43:09.798 line:90% position:50% align:center
and working together as a team.

00:43:09.798 --> 00:43:13.176 line:90% position:50% align:center
The last landmark
we’ll consider in this symposium

00:43:13.176 --> 00:43:16.096 line:90% position:50% align:center
is worshipping together as a family.

00:43:17.180 --> 00:43:19.307 line:90% position:50% align:center
Worshipping together as a family

00:43:19.307 --> 00:43:22.310 line:90% position:50% align:center
promotes peace and brings his blessing.

00:43:22.310 --> 00:43:25.272 line:90% position:50% align:center
Even if not all in your family
are worshippers of Jehovah,

00:43:25.272 --> 00:43:29.317 line:90% position:50% align:center
you can promote peace
by maintaining a very good spiritual routine.

00:43:30.652 --> 00:43:34.322 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the following dramatization,
notice some common obstacles

00:43:34.322 --> 00:43:36.700 line:90% position:50% align:center
to worshipping Jehovah as a family.

00:43:40.579 --> 00:43:41.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hi.

00:43:42.205 --> 00:43:43.540 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, babe.

00:43:43.957 --> 00:43:46.418 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what’s for family worship this week?

00:43:54.009 --> 00:43:56.386 line:90% position:50% align:center
I think I got some good ideas.

00:43:56.386 --> 00:43:57.804 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah?

00:43:57.804 --> 00:43:58.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mm-hmm.

00:43:58.972 --> 00:44:00.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you for reading that.

00:44:00.474 --> 00:44:01.767 line:90% position:50% align:center
Um.

00:44:04.061 --> 00:44:06.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s just go ahead and ask the question.
We’ll just do that.

00:44:06.772 --> 00:44:09.900 line:90% position:50% align:center
So paragraphs 13 and 14:
“How can we be generous?”

00:44:12.444 --> 00:44:14.446 line:90% position:50% align:center
Anybody?

00:44:15.948 --> 00:44:20.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, the footnote that we just read
really helps us to appreciate

00:44:20.285 --> 00:44:23.205 line:90% position:50% align:center
the definition of that quality.

00:44:23.205 --> 00:44:26.125 line:90% position:50% align:center
Without the definition, we’re left to wonder

00:44:26.125 --> 00:44:29.128 line:90% position:50% align:center
exactly what it is
and how it connects to the other things

00:44:29.128 --> 00:44:31.130 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we’ve discussed this evening.

00:44:33.507 --> 00:44:36.010 line:90% position:50% align:center
Gabe, can you go ahead
and read the next one for us?

00:44:36.010 --> 00:44:37.428 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mm-hmm.

00:44:37.428 --> 00:44:38.596 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you.

00:44:40.514 --> 00:44:45.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Bible contains many examples
of submissive individuals.

00:44:46.145 --> 00:44:48.314 line:90% position:50% align:center
So are there examples?

00:44:52.443 --> 00:44:53.360 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sue.

00:44:53.360 --> 00:44:54.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:44:54.069 --> 00:44:55.154 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s right.

00:44:55.154 --> 00:44:57.323 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we talk about examples,
where do we start?

00:44:58.073 --> 00:44:59.742 line:90% position:50% align:center
There are examples in the past;

00:44:59.742 --> 00:45:03.454 line:90% position:50% align:center
there are even examples presently.

00:45:03.454 --> 00:45:07.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we could even be examples.

00:45:07.666 --> 00:45:09.752 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s—that’s the power of them.

00:45:14.548 --> 00:45:16.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s keep going.

00:45:24.767 --> 00:45:26.477 line:90% position:50% align:center
That was a lot of reading.

00:45:26.477 --> 00:45:27.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know, right?

00:45:28.604 --> 00:45:31.148 line:90% position:50% align:center
I want to enjoy family worship, but

00:45:31.148 --> 00:45:34.235 line:90% position:50% align:center
I feel like the things that we are covering

00:45:34.235 --> 00:45:37.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
are just really not what I need right now.

00:45:38.614 --> 00:45:39.949 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:45:41.451 --> 00:45:44.662 line:90% position:50% align:center
You know, I just don’t know
if this is what they need right now.

00:45:44.662 --> 00:45:45.997 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hmm.

00:45:45.997 --> 00:45:47.790 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll keep working on it.

00:45:56.841 --> 00:46:00.386 line:90% position:50% align:center
I think we’d all agree that family worship
was difficult to watch.

00:46:00.386 --> 00:46:02.931 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was uncomfortable for everyone.

00:46:02.931 --> 00:46:05.600 line:90% position:50% align:center
Clearly, Max and Irene had some obstacles

00:46:05.600 --> 00:46:10.605 line:90% position:50% align:center
they needed to overcome
to really worshipping Jehovah as a family.

00:46:10.605 --> 00:46:12.815 line:90% position:50% align:center
To start and keep a good habit going

00:46:12.815 --> 00:46:15.568 line:90% position:50% align:center
requires determination and resolve.

00:46:15.568 --> 00:46:18.071 line:90% position:50% align:center
So that’s where you need
to start for your family.

00:46:18.071 --> 00:46:20.073 line:90% position:50% align:center
You need to resolve

00:46:20.073 --> 00:46:23.118 line:90% position:50% align:center
that you’re going
to worship Jehovah as a family.

00:46:23.118 --> 00:46:25.620 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice the resolve in Joshua’s words

00:46:25.620 --> 00:46:29.165 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Joshua 24:15.

00:46:30.333 --> 00:46:33.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s Joshua 24:15:

00:46:35.338 --> 00:46:38.466 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Now if it seems bad to you to serve Jehovah,

00:46:38.466 --> 00:46:42.637 line:90% position:50% align:center
“choose for yourselves today
whom you will serve,

00:46:42.637 --> 00:46:47.058 line:90% position:50% align:center
“whether the gods that your forefathers
served on the other side of the River

00:46:47.058 --> 00:46:51.062 line:90% position:50% align:center
“or the gods of the Amorites
in whose land you are dwelling.

00:46:51.062 --> 00:46:54.107 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But as for me and my household,

00:46:54.107 --> 00:46:56.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
we will serve Jehovah.”

00:46:58.528 --> 00:47:01.156 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, worship of Jehovah as a family

00:47:01.156 --> 00:47:04.493 line:90% position:50% align:center
needs to be at the very center
of your family life.

00:47:04.493 --> 00:47:06.495 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, weekly family worship

00:47:06.495 --> 00:47:09.664 line:90% position:50% align:center
is not all that’s involved
in worshipping together as a family.

00:47:09.664 --> 00:47:11.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s consider five ways

00:47:11.833 --> 00:47:15.796 line:90% position:50% align:center
we can worship Jehovah together as a family.

00:47:15.796 --> 00:47:18.423 line:90% position:50% align:center
(1) Prayer.

00:47:18.423 --> 00:47:21.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
Parents, do not underestimate the impact

00:47:21.927 --> 00:47:24.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
that your prayers have on your children.

00:47:24.888 --> 00:47:28.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
When a child hears their parents
pour out their hearts to Jehovah,

00:47:28.642 --> 00:47:32.896 line:90% position:50% align:center
that tells them that Jehovah
is very real to their parents.

00:47:32.896 --> 00:47:36.984 line:90% position:50% align:center
I can recall growing up listening
to my father’s prayers.

00:47:36.984 --> 00:47:40.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, when I was young,
I thought his prayers were very long.

00:47:40.988 --> 00:47:45.826 line:90% position:50% align:center
But as I grew older and really
listened carefully to what he was saying,

00:47:45.826 --> 00:47:50.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
I could see how much of a close relationship
he had with Jehovah.

00:47:52.124 --> 00:47:55.044 line:90% position:50% align:center
(2) Discuss the daily text.

00:47:55.044 --> 00:47:57.046 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s an excellent habit

00:47:57.046 --> 00:47:59.673 line:90% position:50% align:center
and a very spiritual way to start the day.

00:48:00.799 --> 00:48:03.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
(3) Attend meetings.

00:48:03.135 --> 00:48:06.472 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, we’re not just making sure our family
is there at the meetings

00:48:06.472 --> 00:48:09.183 line:90% position:50% align:center
but that they’re involved and engaged.

00:48:09.183 --> 00:48:11.894 line:90% position:50% align:center
And work hard to prepare
so that all family members

00:48:11.894 --> 00:48:14.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
can have a meaningful comment
at the meetings.

00:48:15.773 --> 00:48:20.236 line:90% position:50% align:center
(4) Share in the ministry regularly
as a family.

00:48:20.236 --> 00:48:22.863 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, sharing in the ministry together
as a family

00:48:22.863 --> 00:48:25.449 line:90% position:50% align:center
draws us closer to our family members.

00:48:25.449 --> 00:48:28.202 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we hear them speak about the truth,

00:48:28.202 --> 00:48:30.329 line:90% position:50% align:center
we listen to their phone calls,

00:48:30.329 --> 00:48:32.665 line:90% position:50% align:center
or we read their letters,

00:48:32.665 --> 00:48:35.334 line:90% position:50% align:center
we can feel their faith.

00:48:35.334 --> 00:48:37.962 line:90% position:50% align:center
I loved going in the ministry with my mother

00:48:37.962 --> 00:48:41.048 line:90% position:50% align:center
and listening to her skillfully use the Bible

00:48:41.048 --> 00:48:43.050 line:90% position:50% align:center
to answer questions.

00:48:44.010 --> 00:48:46.971 line:90% position:50% align:center
And (5) have a consistent,

00:48:46.971 --> 00:48:51.350 line:90% position:50% align:center
enjoyable,
and meaningful Family Worship program.

00:48:51.350 --> 00:48:55.062 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s consider what that means
—first of all, consistent.

00:48:55.062 --> 00:48:57.481 line:90% position:50% align:center
