00:55:50.606 --> 00:55:53.693 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what a difference their efforts to listen

00:55:53.693 --> 00:55:55.945 line:90% position:50% align:center
and really understand what was happening

00:55:55.945 --> 00:55:59.282 line:90% position:50% align:center
with the kids made in the family worship!

00:55:59.282 --> 00:56:03.911 line:90% position:50% align:center
How did Max and Irene
make family worship more enjoyable?

00:56:03.911 --> 00:56:08.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
Did you see how the family
was reacting at family worship now?

00:56:08.082 --> 00:56:10.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
What a difference!

00:56:10.084 --> 00:56:12.128 line:90% position:50% align:center
The kids were smiling.

00:56:12.128 --> 00:56:14.339 line:90% position:50% align:center
They looked engaged in the discussion

00:56:14.339 --> 00:56:17.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
and touched by what they were discussing.

00:56:17.634 --> 00:56:20.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
So do what you can
to make sure that your family

00:56:20.845 --> 00:56:23.139 line:90% position:50% align:center
feels relaxed and happy

00:56:23.139 --> 00:56:25.516 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that your family worship reflects

00:56:25.516 --> 00:56:28.770 line:90% position:50% align:center
the kind of happy
and joyful God that Jehovah is.

00:56:28.770 --> 00:56:31.648 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remember, your family will often remember

00:56:31.648 --> 00:56:34.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
more about how they felt
during family worship

00:56:34.818 --> 00:56:38.363 line:90% position:50% align:center
than maybe the exact details
of what they learned.

00:56:39.948 --> 00:56:42.367 line:90% position:50% align:center
Keep worshipping Jehovah as a family.

00:56:42.367 --> 00:56:44.744 line:90% position:50% align:center
Make your family worship consistent,

00:56:44.744 --> 00:56:47.330 line:90% position:50% align:center
enjoyable, and meaningful.

00:56:47.330 --> 00:56:51.418 line:90% position:50% align:center
And work together to overcome obstacles,

00:56:51.418 --> 00:56:56.381 line:90% position:50% align:center
just like Max and Irene and the kids
all worked together to solve problems

00:56:56.381 --> 00:56:59.426 line:90% position:50% align:center
and create a very peaceful family life.

00:56:59.426 --> 00:57:01.970 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was really beautiful to see how far

00:57:01.970 --> 00:57:04.556 line:90% position:50% align:center
they had come by applying Bible principles.

00:57:05.849 --> 00:57:09.060 line:90% position:50% align:center
In review, this symposium has taught us

00:57:09.060 --> 00:57:11.313 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Bible principles can be used

00:57:11.313 --> 00:57:14.482 line:90% position:50% align:center
as a road map to family peace.

00:57:14.482 --> 00:57:17.402 line:90% position:50% align:center
Work hard to show love and respect,

00:57:17.402 --> 00:57:21.281 line:90% position:50% align:center
to improve communication,
to work together as a team,

00:57:21.281 --> 00:57:24.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to worship Jehovah together.

00:57:24.576 --> 00:57:28.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
And please be patient with one another

00:57:28.246 --> 00:57:31.541 line:90% position:50% align:center
as you form habits that lead to peace.

00:57:31.541 --> 00:57:33.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
With Jehovah’s help, you and your family

00:57:33.877 --> 00:57:37.589 line:90% position:50% align:center
will enjoy peace that only he can provide.

00:57:39.800 --> 00:57:41.259 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you, brothers.

00:57:41.259 --> 00:57:44.263 line:90% position:50% align:center
We benefited from thinking
about how we can apply

00:57:44.263 --> 00:57:46.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
the Bible principles you shared

00:57:46.431 --> 00:57:50.686 line:90% position:50% align:center
and from the practical lessons
in the dramatizations.

00:57:52.187 --> 00:57:56.483 line:90% position:50% align:center
All of us long to see true peace on earth.

00:57:56.483 --> 00:57:58.777 line:90% position:50% align:center
How will that be accomplished?

00:57:58.777 --> 00:58:01.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
And how can we prove
that we honor and support

00:58:01.572 --> 00:58:05.451 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah’s appointed King, Christ Jesus?

00:58:05.451 --> 00:58:10.205 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s listen as Brother Mark Noumair,
a helper to the Teaching Committee,

00:58:10.205 --> 00:58:13.959 line:90% position:50% align:center
provides these answers and more in the talk,

00:58:13.959 --> 00:58:17.129 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Loyally Support the ‘Prince of Peace.’”

00:58:25.179 --> 00:58:29.141 line:90% position:50% align:center
Imagine the scene: It’s nighttime.

00:58:29.141 --> 00:58:34.063 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re in the garden of Gethsemane
with your close friends and beloved Teacher.

00:58:34.063 --> 00:58:37.274 line:90% position:50% align:center
Suddenly, you hear a crowd coming.

00:58:37.274 --> 00:58:41.070 line:90% position:50% align:center
They’re being led by a man you know,
Judas Iscariot.

00:58:41.070 --> 00:58:44.782 line:90% position:50% align:center
He approaches Jesus
and kisses him on the cheek.

00:58:44.782 --> 00:58:49.745 line:90% position:50% align:center
He then steps aside
as men move in to arrest Jesus.

00:58:49.745 --> 00:58:52.081 line:90% position:50% align:center
Your emotions churn inside you.

00:58:52.081 --> 00:58:55.918 line:90% position:50% align:center
Your Master and Lord is being arrested
—the Son of God.

00:58:55.918 --> 00:58:57.753 line:90% position:50% align:center
How can this be happening?

00:58:57.753 --> 00:58:59.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
What do you do?

00:58:59.255 --> 00:59:02.633 line:90% position:50% align:center
Before you can even decide what to do,

00:59:02.633 --> 00:59:04.635 line:90% position:50% align:center
Peter draws his sword

00:59:04.635 --> 00:59:07.638 line:90% position:50% align:center
and chops off the ear
of the slave of the high priest.

00:59:08.639 --> 00:59:11.434 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then Jesus says to Peter:

00:59:11.434 --> 00:59:15.855 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Return your sword to its place,

00:59:15.855 --> 00:59:20.568 line:90% position:50% align:center
for all those who take up the sword
will perish by the sword.”

00:59:21.527 --> 00:59:24.739 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then you watch the unbelievable,

00:59:24.739 --> 00:59:28.534 line:90% position:50% align:center
as Jesus heals the man’s ear.

00:59:28.534 --> 00:59:31.370 line:90% position:50% align:center
Peter must have thought
that it was a great and noble thing

00:59:31.370 --> 00:59:34.540 line:90% position:50% align:center
to fight on behalf of the Son of God.

00:59:34.540 --> 00:59:36.918 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Jesus didn’t think so.

00:59:36.918 --> 00:59:39.045 line:90% position:50% align:center
With six words

00:59:39.045 --> 00:59:43.424 line:90% position:50% align:center
—“return your sword to its place”—

00:59:43.424 --> 00:59:46.552 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus taught his disciples
an important lesson.

00:59:47.929 --> 00:59:50.265 line:90% position:50% align:center
This was not their fight;

00:59:50.265 --> 00:59:52.559 line:90% position:50% align:center
nor was it the time to fight.

00:59:53.977 --> 00:59:56.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
So in this talk,

00:59:56.396 --> 01:00:00.608 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’re going to focus our attention
on an insidious way

01:00:00.608 --> 01:00:03.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
that any of us, like Peter,

01:00:03.611 --> 01:00:08.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
can become inadvertently involved
in this world’s conflicts

01:00:08.533 --> 01:00:10.869 line:90% position:50% align:center
without even realizing it.

01:00:10.869 --> 01:00:15.415 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we will talk about how we
can avoid making that serious mistake.

01:00:16.541 --> 01:00:18.543 line:90% position:50% align:center
But first,

01:00:18.543 --> 01:00:22.464 line:90% position:50% align:center
let’s discuss why Jesus
did not ask his Father

01:00:22.464 --> 01:00:25.258 line:90% position:50% align:center
to send “12 legions of angels”

01:00:25.258 --> 01:00:27.719 line:90% position:50% align:center
to help him when being arrested.

01:00:27.719 --> 01:00:31.723 line:90% position:50% align:center
It has to do with Jesus’ name.

01:00:31.723 --> 01:00:35.393 line:90% position:50% align:center
So please open your Bible
to Isaiah chapter 9,

01:00:35.393 --> 01:00:38.647 line:90% position:50% align:center
and let’s read verse 6

01:00:38.647 --> 01:00:42.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Isaiah 9:6.

01:00:42.192 --> 01:00:46.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, we know Jesus has many titles,

01:00:46.112 --> 01:00:50.450 line:90% position:50% align:center
but in this verse,
we’re going to focus on just one.

01:00:50.450 --> 01:00:53.787 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verse 6:

01:00:53.787 --> 01:00:56.873 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For a child has been born to us,

01:00:56.873 --> 01:00:59.418 line:90% position:50% align:center
“a son has been given to us;

01:00:59.418 --> 01:01:02.546 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and the rulership will rest on his shoulder.

01:01:02.546 --> 01:01:05.173 line:90% position:50% align:center
“His name will be called Wonderful Counselor,

01:01:05.173 --> 01:01:07.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Mighty God, Eternal Father,

01:01:07.301 --> 01:01:09.928 line:90% position:50% align:center
Prince of Peace.”

01:01:10.846 --> 01:01:15.058 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why is Jesus called “Prince of Peace”?

01:01:15.058 --> 01:01:19.980 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, consider what Jehovah’s angel
 declared to the shepherds in the field

01:01:19.980 --> 01:01:24.485 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Jesus’ birth at Luke 2:14.

01:01:24.485 --> 01:01:27.946 line:90% position:50% align:center
They said:
“Glory in the heights above to God,

01:01:27.946 --> 01:01:32.493 line:90% position:50% align:center
and on earth peace among men of goodwill.”

01:01:32.493 --> 01:01:35.120 line:90% position:50% align:center
How appropriate for the angels to announce

01:01:35.120 --> 01:01:37.831 line:90% position:50% align:center
that at the birth
of the destined Prince of Peace,

01:01:37.831 --> 01:01:41.960 line:90% position:50% align:center
there would be divine peace
for those who have God’s goodwill!

01:01:43.337 --> 01:01:46.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
But when will this become a reality?

01:01:46.215 --> 01:01:48.801 line:90% position:50% align:center
It didn’t happen when Jesus was on earth,

01:01:48.801 --> 01:01:51.679 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we certainly don’t see peace today.

01:01:51.679 --> 01:01:53.806 line:90% position:50% align:center
Instead of peace, what do we see?

01:01:53.806 --> 01:01:57.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
We see the nations that are locked
in hostilities and aggression

01:01:57.101 --> 01:01:59.853 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a competition for world dominance.

01:01:59.853 --> 01:02:03.148 line:90% position:50% align:center
We see global violence and bloodshed.

01:02:03.148 --> 01:02:06.819 line:90% position:50% align:center
But please don’t lose heart.

01:02:06.819 --> 01:02:11.073 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because we don’t see peace now
does not mean it’s not coming.

01:02:11.073 --> 01:02:13.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
Isaiah 9:6

01:02:13.993 --> 01:02:16.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
—it’s not just wishful thinking.

01:02:16.328 --> 01:02:21.125 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s a promise from Almighty God,
and Jehovah cannot lie.

01:02:21.125 --> 01:02:23.210 line:90% position:50% align:center
All his prophecies come true.

01:02:23.210 --> 01:02:27.214 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact,
let’s read the last portion of verse 7

01:02:27.214 --> 01:02:29.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
in Isaiah chapter 9.

01:02:29.592 --> 01:02:34.013 line:90% position:50% align:center
The last verse
(the last portion of verse 7) says:

01:02:34.013 --> 01:02:37.725 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The zeal of Jehovah of armies will do this.”

01:02:37.725 --> 01:02:39.727 line:90% position:50% align:center
What does that mean?

01:02:39.727 --> 01:02:42.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
It means that Jehovah
does nothing in a half-hearted way.

01:02:42.688 --> 01:02:45.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
He’s zealous to bring peace, and he will.

01:02:45.316 --> 01:02:48.945 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can be sure
that whatever Jehovah promises,

01:02:48.945 --> 01:02:50.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
he will fully accomplish.

01:02:53.157 --> 01:02:55.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
So how will peace come to the earth?

01:02:56.619 --> 01:02:59.205 line:90% position:50% align:center
Did the Prince of Peace give us a clue?

01:02:59.205 --> 01:03:00.748 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, he did.

01:03:00.748 --> 01:03:03.793 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, the key to everlasting peace

01:03:03.793 --> 01:03:07.130 line:90% position:50% align:center
is on the lips of millions of people
throughout the world.

01:03:07.130 --> 01:03:09.590 line:90% position:50% align:center
They know it by heart.

01:03:09.590 --> 01:03:14.554 line:90% position:50% align:center
But let’s read it at Matthew 6:9, 10

01:03:17.849 --> 01:03:21.060 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Matthew 6:9.

01:03:21.060 --> 01:03:23.062 line:90% position:50% align:center
What a beautiful thought for us!

01:03:23.062 --> 01:03:25.899 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is how everlasting peace
is going to come through.

01:03:25.899 --> 01:03:30.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
It depends on the fulfillment
of these verses.

01:03:30.069 --> 01:03:32.071 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verse 9:

01:03:32.071 --> 01:03:36.201 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You must pray, then, this way:
‘Our Father in the heavens,

01:03:36.201 --> 01:03:41.206 line:90% position:50% align:center
let your name [the name Jehovah]
be sanctified.’”

01:03:41.206 --> 01:03:44.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
The emphasis that we place
on the name of God

01:03:44.084 --> 01:03:46.961 line:90% position:50% align:center
is not merely a matter
of religious knowledge.

01:03:46.961 --> 01:03:49.089 line:90% position:50% align:center
Everyone must know God’s name

01:03:49.089 --> 01:03:52.342 line:90% position:50% align:center
and treat it as something holy and respected.

01:03:52.342 --> 01:03:54.844 line:90% position:50% align:center
It has to be something sacred.

01:03:54.844 --> 01:03:58.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
It must be cleared of all the reproach
that has been heaped upon it.

01:03:59.474 --> 01:04:04.437 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, the well-being
of the entire universe and its inhabitants

01:04:04.437 --> 01:04:08.692 line:90% position:50% align:center
depends upon the sanctification
of Jehovah’s name.

01:04:10.110 --> 01:04:12.904 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, let’s look at verse 10:

01:04:12.904 --> 01:04:15.699 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Let your Kingdom come.

01:04:15.699 --> 01:04:20.370 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let your will take place,
as in heaven, also on earth.”

01:04:21.663 --> 01:04:26.626 line:90% position:50% align:center
God’s Kingdom
—two words but so important.

01:04:27.669 --> 01:04:31.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
God’s Kingdom
is the most powerful government

01:04:31.256 --> 01:04:33.508 line:90% position:50% align:center
humanity will ever see.

01:04:33.508 --> 01:04:35.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
There is no nation or empire

01:04:35.510 --> 01:04:39.765 line:90% position:50% align:center
that can withstand
the might of God’s Kingdom.

01:04:39.765 --> 01:04:44.686 line:90% position:50% align:center
And any nation who thinks
they can block the coming of God’s Kingdom

01:04:44.686 --> 01:04:49.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
is like an ant who plants itself firmly
on the railroad track

01:04:49.691 --> 01:04:54.238 line:90% position:50% align:center
and with his hand raised defiantly
shouts to the oncoming locomotive:

01:04:54.238 --> 01:04:56.990 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Stop! You can’t run over me.”

01:04:58.200 --> 01:05:00.452 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, God’s heavenly government has the power

01:05:00.452 --> 01:05:03.288 line:90% position:50% align:center
to destroy all present-day violent regimes.

01:05:03.288 --> 01:05:06.083 line:90% position:50% align:center
They’re like ants to Jehovah.

01:05:06.083 --> 01:05:08.085 line:90% position:50% align:center
And he will eliminate their ability

01:05:08.085 --> 01:05:12.006 line:90% position:50% align:center
to wage war, to foment conflict,
and to shed blood.

01:05:12.923 --> 01:05:14.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, yes, Matthew 6:9, 10

01:05:14.925 --> 01:05:18.762 line:90% position:50% align:center
—it’s that valuable and important
for lasting peace.

01:05:18.762 --> 01:05:23.058 line:90% position:50% align:center
God’s Kingdom is the only road
to lasting peace.

01:05:23.058 --> 01:05:26.729 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in his role as King,

01:05:26.729 --> 01:05:31.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
Revelation 19:15 describes Jesus

01:05:31.192 --> 01:05:35.154 line:90% position:50% align:center
as ‘striking the nations with an iron rod.’

01:05:35.154 --> 01:05:38.866 line:90% position:50% align:center
Soon, Jehovah will give
the command to his Son,

01:05:38.866 --> 01:05:43.829 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he will destroy
all the things that disrupt peace.

01:05:43.829 --> 01:05:47.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
Gone will be the terror
that we have grown accustomed to living with

01:05:47.416 --> 01:05:49.794 line:90% position:50% align:center
day in and day out.

01:05:51.837 --> 01:05:54.382 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what will happen next?

01:05:54.382 --> 01:05:56.759 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is what will happen

01:05:56.759 --> 01:05:59.220 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Psalm 37:10, 11.

01:05:59.220 --> 01:06:02.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s open our Bibles here
to Psalm 37:10, 11,

01:06:02.682 --> 01:06:05.393 line:90% position:50% align:center
and just allow this prophecy to absorb

01:06:05.393 --> 01:06:07.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to thrill our minds and our hearts

01:06:07.395 --> 01:06:11.315 line:90% position:50% align:center
and give us a hope for the future.

01:06:12.525 --> 01:06:15.903 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verse 10 of Psalm 37:

01:06:15.903 --> 01:06:18.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Just a little while longer,

01:06:18.406 --> 01:06:23.244 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and the wicked will be no more
[a little while longer];

01:06:23.244 --> 01:06:27.665 line:90% position:50% align:center
you will look at where they were,
and they will not be there.”

01:06:27.665 --> 01:06:29.208 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Just a little while longer.”

01:06:29.208 --> 01:06:31.294 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s just like children saying
to their parents

01:06:31.294 --> 01:06:33.338 line:90% position:50% align:center
when going on a trip
“Are we there yet?”

01:06:33.338 --> 01:06:36.591 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the parents say
“Just a little while longer.”

01:06:36.591 --> 01:06:40.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that brings comfort to them,
and it’s the same with us.

01:06:42.221 --> 01:06:44.223 line:90% position:50% align:center
So imagine that!

01:06:44.223 --> 01:06:46.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
This means you go into the streets,

01:06:46.351 --> 01:06:48.353 line:90% position:50% align:center
you’re looking for a wicked person,

01:06:48.353 --> 01:06:50.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
and you will not be able to find even one.

01:06:50.688 --> 01:06:54.317 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The wicked will be no more.”

01:06:54.317 --> 01:06:56.903 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But the meek will possess the earth.”

01:06:56.903 --> 01:06:59.072 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s what we’re speaking about in verse 11.

01:06:59.072 --> 01:07:03.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s read that:
“But the meek will possess the earth,

01:07:03.409 --> 01:07:08.289 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they will find exquisite delight
in the abundance of peace.”

01:07:09.249 --> 01:07:11.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
We love reading that.

01:07:11.668 --> 01:07:13.795 line:90% position:50% align:center
Men will be at peace.

01:07:13.795 --> 01:07:17.048 line:90% position:50% align:center
They will be at peace with themselves,
with their neighbors, with their God.

01:07:17.048 --> 01:07:18.550 line:90% position:50% align:center
How does that sound to you?

01:07:18.550 --> 01:07:20.802 line:90% position:50% align:center
Meditate on that.

01:07:20.802 --> 01:07:24.639 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can you see yourself there
in a peaceful new world

01:07:24.639 --> 01:07:26.641 line:90% position:50% align:center
where the only news to tune into

01:07:26.641 --> 01:07:29.394 line:90% position:50% align:center
is regarding who’s getting resurrected today

01:07:29.394 --> 01:07:33.565 line:90% position:50% align:center
or which new person you will be assigned
to teach about Jehovah?

01:07:33.565 --> 01:07:36.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can you imagine the joy
of studying with a person,

01:07:36.193 --> 01:07:38.320 line:90% position:50% align:center
not just from a different culture,

01:07:38.320 --> 01:07:40.697 line:90% position:50% align:center
but from a different time period,

01:07:40.697 --> 01:07:43.450 line:90% position:50% align:center
seeing things through their eyes

01:07:43.450 --> 01:07:46.495 line:90% position:50% align:center
as they come to love Jehovah as you do?

01:07:48.246 --> 01:07:50.791 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, soon the Prince of Peace

01:07:50.791 --> 01:07:54.836 line:90% position:50% align:center
will turn this world
into one of sheer delight

01:07:54.836 --> 01:07:58.131 line:90% position:50% align:center
—no more borders,
no more threats, no more worries—

01:07:58.131 --> 01:08:01.969 line:90% position:50% align:center
just an abundance of peace
with your brothers and sisters.

01:08:03.428 --> 01:08:05.889 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you want to be there?

01:08:05.889 --> 01:08:08.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
Me too.

01:08:08.100 --> 01:08:13.105 line:90% position:50% align:center
So how can we show our loyal support
for the Prince of Peace?

01:08:13.105 --> 01:08:15.357 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please watch the following video,

01:08:15.357 --> 01:08:19.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
and notice the different ways
we can do this right now.

01:08:23.574 --> 01:08:26.243 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I am no part of the world.”

01:08:30.164 --> 01:08:34.126 line:90% position:50% align:center
But is the world a part of me?

01:08:36.712 --> 01:08:39.715 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m pressured every day

01:08:39.715 --> 01:08:43.594 line:90% position:50% align:center
to get involved in political issues
that affect me socially,

01:08:51.018 --> 01:08:54.605 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . environmentally,

01:09:00.027 --> 01:09:02.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . and economically.

01:09:09.870 --> 01:09:14.333 line:90% position:50% align:center
That pressure could rob me
of my peace of mind

01:09:17.044 --> 01:09:19.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . and influence how I think.

01:09:19.296 --> 01:09:21.757 line:90% position:50% align:center
I could take sides in my heart,

01:09:21.757 --> 01:09:24.719 line:90% position:50% align:center
even if I’m not aware of it.

01:09:32.226 --> 01:09:35.104 line:90% position:50% align:center
But I know that Jehovah

01:09:35.104 --> 01:09:38.065 line:90% position:50% align:center
will care for all of mankind’s concerns

01:10:05.760 --> 01:10:07.762 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . by means of his Kingdom

01:10:07.762 --> 01:10:11.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
ruled by his Son, Jesus Christ.

01:10:14.227 --> 01:10:18.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
I show my support for him
in my prayers,

01:10:19.482 --> 01:10:22.735 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . in how I think and feel,

01:10:32.036 --> 01:10:34.122 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . and by teaching others

01:10:34.122 --> 01:10:36.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
what the Kingdom will do for mankind.

01:10:37.500 --> 01:10:39.711 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know there are millions

01:10:39.711 --> 01:10:43.089 line:90% position:50% align:center
of brothers and sisters
all over the world

01:10:43.089 --> 01:10:46.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . who loyally support
the “Prince of Peace”

01:10:46.217 --> 01:10:48.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
just like me, because I

01:10:49.888 --> 01:10:51.890 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . I

01:10:52.766 --> 01:10:56.770 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . I am no part of the world.

01:11:01.483 --> 01:11:05.028 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what takes away the peace
in the country where you live?

01:11:05.028 --> 01:11:08.448 line:90% position:50% align:center
in your community?
in your town? in your society?

01:11:08.448 --> 01:11:12.828 line:90% position:50% align:center
Most likely,
it’s the hot-button social issues.

01:11:12.828 --> 01:11:15.080 line:90% position:50% align:center
Did you notice
how our two brothers and sister

01:11:15.080 --> 01:11:18.417 line:90% position:50% align:center
showed their loyal support
for the Prince of Peace?

01:11:18.417 --> 01:11:20.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
What issues affected them?

01:11:20.419 --> 01:11:25.382 line:90% position:50% align:center
Unfair tax hikes, blatant injustice,
a disregard of the environment

01:11:25.382 --> 01:11:30.387 line:90% position:50% align:center
—all things in themselves seemed
like noble causes worthy to get involved.

01:11:30.387 --> 01:11:32.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘How can they get away with this?

01:11:32.431 --> 01:11:35.183 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s not right.
We should do something.’

01:11:35.183 --> 01:11:37.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
Does that sound familiar?

01:11:37.227 --> 01:11:40.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
We may not have a literal sword in our hand,

01:11:40.564 --> 01:11:43.650 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we all have our Peterlike moments.

01:11:43.650 --> 01:11:47.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if we’re not careful,
issues that are close to our heart

01:11:47.279 --> 01:11:51.575 line:90% position:50% align:center
can charge our emotions
and we can lose our spiritual balance.

01:11:51.575 --> 01:11:55.579 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what can help us
when we see things that are wrong?

01:11:55.579 --> 01:11:58.415 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remember what the Prince of Peace
said to Peter

01:11:58.415 --> 01:12:00.959 line:90% position:50% align:center
in that highly charged moment:

01:12:00.959 --> 01:12:05.214 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Return your sword to its place.”

01:12:05.214 --> 01:12:08.467 line:90% position:50% align:center
In other words, this is not your fight.

01:12:08.467 --> 01:12:10.094 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what do we do?

01:12:10.094 --> 01:12:12.846 line:90% position:50% align:center
We do something far better than fight.

01:12:12.846 --> 01:12:14.473 line:90% position:50% align:center
We preach.

01:12:14.473 --> 01:12:17.268 line:90% position:50% align:center
Each time that we share the Kingdom news,

01:12:17.268 --> 01:12:20.938 line:90% position:50% align:center
we proclaim our support for Jesus’ rule.

01:12:20.938 --> 01:12:23.357 line:90% position:50% align:center
But here’s the thing:

01:12:23.357 --> 01:12:26.986 line:90% position:50% align:center
If we truly believe
in the good news of the Kingdom,

01:12:26.986 --> 01:12:31.240 line:90% position:50% align:center
we will not do anything
that hinders our ability to tell it.

01:12:31.240 --> 01:12:33.868 line:90% position:50% align:center
Once again, it’s so important

01:12:33.868 --> 01:12:37.913 line:90% position:50% align:center
that if we truly believe
in the good news of the Kingdom,

01:12:37.913 --> 01:12:42.918 line:90% position:50% align:center
we will not do anything
that hinders our ability to tell it.

01:12:42.918 --> 01:12:44.003 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

01:12:44.003 --> 01:12:45.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, let’s find out.

01:12:45.296 --> 01:12:47.423 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s open up to Peter’s words himself

01:12:47.423 --> 01:12:51.594 line:90% position:50% align:center
at 1 Peter 2:12

01:12:53.763 --> 01:12:56.891 line:90% position:50% align:center
—1 Peter 2:12.

01:12:56.891 --> 01:12:59.352 line:90% position:50% align:center
Peter helps us here with why we need

01:12:59.352 --> 01:13:03.189 line:90% position:50% align:center
to maintain our conduct properly.

01:13:03.189 --> 01:13:05.233 line:90% position:50% align:center
First Peter 2:12:

01:13:05.233 --> 01:13:08.778 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Maintain your conduct fine
among the nations,

01:13:08.778 --> 01:13:11.906 line:90% position:50% align:center
“so that when they accuse you
of being wrongdoers,

01:13:11.906 --> 01:13:14.784 line:90% position:50% align:center
“they may be eyewitnesses
of your fine works

01:13:14.784 --> 01:13:19.789 line:90% position:50% align:center
and, as a result,
glorify God in the day of his inspection.”

01:13:20.540 --> 01:13:23.042 line:90% position:50% align:center
So Peter had to learn this.

01:13:23.042 --> 01:13:25.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
But do we see the connection?

01:13:25.378 --> 01:13:29.424 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our actions and words
are directly linked to Jehovah.

01:13:29.424 --> 01:13:34.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
When people see us,
they see a people that worships Jehovah.

01:13:34.095 --> 01:13:38.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
And when people hear us,
they hear a people that worships Jehovah.

01:13:39.559 --> 01:13:43.438 line:90% position:50% align:center
Imagine how our freeness of speech
to speak about God’s Kingdom

01:13:43.438 --> 01:13:48.443 line:90% position:50% align:center
would be hindered if we were to voice
a position for a political issue!

01:13:48.443 --> 01:13:50.695 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it can happen so easily.

01:13:50.695 --> 01:13:55.116 line:90% position:50% align:center
It can happen at work, at school,
with relatives, and so forth.

01:13:55.116 --> 01:13:57.952 line:90% position:50% align:center
Satan sets the trap masterfully.

01:13:57.952 --> 01:13:59.579 line:90% position:50% align:center
He’s just waiting.

01:13:59.579 --> 01:14:03.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
If he could only make us
“chop off the ear” of anything in this world

01:14:03.833 --> 01:14:07.087 line:90% position:50% align:center
that causes hurt and indignation in our heart

01:14:07.087 --> 01:14:11.675 line:90% position:50% align:center
or if he can hook our heartstrings
by getting us emotionally charged,

01:14:11.675 --> 01:14:15.345 line:90% position:50% align:center
he can then step back and reel us in.

01:14:15.345 --> 01:14:18.265 line:90% position:50% align:center
The new world, our hope for true peace,

01:14:18.265 --> 01:14:21.560 line:90% position:50% align:center
all starts to fade into the background.

01:14:21.560 --> 01:14:24.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
Don’t give him that chance!

01:14:24.396 --> 01:14:26.398 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be determined to do

01:14:26.398 --> 01:14:30.610 line:90% position:50% align:center
what Titus 3:1, 2 tells us.

01:14:30.610 --> 01:14:33.446 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s read that

01:14:33.446 --> 01:14:37.826 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Titus chapter 3,

01:14:37.826 --> 01:14:39.828 line:90% position:50% align:center
verses 1 and 2.

01:14:39.828 --> 01:14:42.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here is the Scriptural admonition:

01:14:45.042 --> 01:14:48.420 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Continue reminding them to be in subjection

01:14:48.420 --> 01:14:52.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and to be obedient
to governments and authorities,

01:14:52.257 --> 01:14:54.676 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to be ready for every good work,

01:14:54.676 --> 01:14:59.556 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to speak injuriously of no one,
not to be quarrelsome,

01:14:59.556 --> 01:15:03.769 line:90% position:50% align:center
but to be reasonable,
displaying all mildness toward all men.”

01:15:05.062 --> 01:15:07.105 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Be in subjection

01:15:07.105 --> 01:15:10.567 line:90% position:50% align:center
and be obedient
to governments and authorities.’

01:15:10.567 --> 01:15:12.236 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, now let’s break that down.

01:15:12.236 --> 01:15:14.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
In practical terms, what does it mean?

01:15:14.696 --> 01:15:18.867 line:90% position:50% align:center
It means to obey the laws of the land
and pay taxes,

01:15:18.867 --> 01:15:22.871 line:90% position:50% align:center
to not speak negatively
about the superior authorities,

01:15:22.871 --> 01:15:25.916 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to be careful not to take sides
on political issues

01:15:25.916 --> 01:15:28.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
(not even in our hearts).

01:15:28.377 --> 01:15:31.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you remember
that expression from the video?

01:15:31.505 --> 01:15:33.632 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I am no part of the world.

01:15:33.632 --> 01:15:36.885 line:90% position:50% align:center
But is the world a part of me?”

01:15:36.885 --> 01:15:38.887 line:90% position:50% align:center
Of course,
when we find ourselves

01:15:38.887 --> 01:15:42.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
between Caesar’s law and God’s law,
we know what to do.

01:15:42.099 --> 01:15:46.979 line:90% position:50% align:center
We apply Acts 5:29
and “obey God as ruler rather than men.”

01:15:46.979 --> 01:15:48.981 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know that.

01:15:48.981 --> 01:15:53.235 line:90% position:50% align:center
But like Jesus, who healed the ear
of the armed guard Malchus,

01:15:53.235 --> 01:15:55.654 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’re determined to react with mildness

01:15:55.654 --> 01:16:00.659 line:90% position:50% align:center
when provoked by an injustice
or cruelty in this world.

01:16:02.787 --> 01:16:04.789 line:90% position:50% align:center
In conclusion,

01:16:04.789 --> 01:16:09.794 line:90% position:50% align:center
we have the indescribable privilege
to honor the Prince of Peace.

01:16:09.794 --> 01:16:14.799 line:90% position:50% align:center
And how reassuring it is to know
that Jesus understands our feelings!

01:16:14.799 --> 01:16:19.804 line:90% position:50% align:center
He understands our emotions
when we see things that we know are wrong.

01:16:19.804 --> 01:16:22.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
He knows these things hurt our heart.

01:16:22.932 --> 01:16:24.934 line:90% position:50% align:center
We just want to make things right.

01:16:26.060 --> 01:16:28.563 line:90% position:50% align:center
But remember the critical lesson

01:16:28.563 --> 01:16:32.358 line:90% position:50% align:center
he taught his apostles
in the garden of Gethsemane:

01:16:32.358 --> 01:16:35.945 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is not your fight.

01:16:38.489 --> 01:16:43.119 line:90% position:50% align:center
Rather, Jehovah, the King of Eternity,
and Jesus, the Prince of Peace,

01:16:43.119 --> 01:16:47.957 line:90% position:50% align:center
are telling us:
“This is our fight. Leave it in our hands.”

01:16:47.957 --> 01:16:51.919 line:90% position:50% align:center
Soon, the prophecy at Isaiah 9:6, 7

01:16:51.919 --> 01:16:54.589 line:90% position:50% align:center
will be fulfilled completely.

01:16:54.589 --> 01:16:57.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the meantime,
keep preaching about the Kingdom.

01:16:57.925 --> 01:16:59.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
Avoid saying or doing anything

01:16:59.927 --> 01:17:03.723 line:90% position:50% align:center
that suggests taking sides
on a political issue.

01:17:03.723 --> 01:17:06.184 line:90% position:50% align:center
Don’t allow yourself to “chop off the ear”

01:17:06.184 --> 01:17:10.271 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the injustices and the causes of conflict
of this old world.

01:17:10.271 --> 01:17:13.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
Peter tried that, but it didn’t work.

01:17:13.691 --> 01:17:16.694 line:90% position:50% align:center
He learned a big lesson
that day in the garden,

01:17:16.694 --> 01:17:18.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he never forgot it.

01:17:18.696 --> 01:17:21.157 line:90% position:50% align:center
May we never forget it either.

01:17:21.157 --> 01:17:24.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now is the time to show
your active and loyal support

01:17:24.702 --> 01:17:26.746 line:90% position:50% align:center
for the Prince of Peace

01:17:26.746 --> 01:17:31.751 line:90% position:50% align:center
as we echo Peter’s words at 2 Peter 3:14

01:17:31.751 --> 01:17:36.673 line:90% position:50% align:center
and “do [our] utmost to be found finally
by [Jehovah and the Prince of Peace]

01:17:36.673 --> 01:17:40.677 line:90% position:50% align:center
spotless and unblemished and in peace.”

01:17:42.470 --> 01:17:45.849 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you, Brother Noumair,
for strengthening our determination

01:17:45.849 --> 01:17:47.851 line:90% position:50% align:center
to give our undivided support

01:17:47.851 --> 01:17:51.271 line:90% position:50% align:center
to God’s appointed King, Christ Jesus.

01:17:52.522 --> 01:17:55.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
This brings us
to the final talk of today’s session.

01:17:57.235 --> 01:18:01.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus promised to give his followers peace.

01:18:01.656 --> 01:18:05.660 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why is the peace that Jesus gives
far superior

01:18:05.660 --> 01:18:09.247 line:90% position:50% align:center
to any peace that this world promises?

01:18:09.247 --> 01:18:12.793 line:90% position:50% align:center
And how can we safeguard the gift of peace

01:18:12.793 --> 01:18:14.878 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jesus has given us?

01:18:16.546 --> 01:18:20.050 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please follow along
as Brother Anthony Morris,

01:18:20.050 --> 01:18:22.052 line:90% position:50% align:center
a member of the Governing Body,

01:18:22.052 --> 01:18:26.974 line:90% position:50% align:center
delivers the talk,
“Do Not Be Misled by Imitation Peace!”

01:18:34.940 --> 01:18:37.943 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus taught us that Satan

01:18:37.943 --> 01:18:40.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
is “the father of the lie.”

01:18:41.822 --> 01:18:45.451 line:90% position:50% align:center
We recall that he deceived Eve,
a perfect woman.

01:18:46.410 --> 01:18:50.998 line:90% position:50% align:center
He lied about our precious Jehovah.

01:18:50.998 --> 01:18:55.294 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, you’re familiar (many of you)
with Revelation chapter 12.

01:18:55.294 --> 01:18:57.504 line:90% position:50% align:center
I invite you to find that

01:18:57.504 --> 01:19:00.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Revelation chapter 12.

01:19:00.549 --> 01:19:04.386 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in this chapter, verses 7 and 8,

01:19:04.386 --> 01:19:07.806 line:90% position:50% align:center
it addressed the fact
that “war broke out in heaven.”

01:19:07.806 --> 01:19:09.808 line:90% position:50% align:center
But notice

01:19:09.808 --> 01:19:13.479 line:90% position:50% align:center
that after he’s kicked out of heaven,

01:19:13.479 --> 01:19:15.272 line:90% position:50% align:center
in verse 9 we read:

01:19:15.272 --> 01:19:18.943 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So down the great dragon was hurled,

01:19:18.943 --> 01:19:23.280 line:90% position:50% align:center
“the original serpent,
the one called Devil and Satan,

01:19:23.280 --> 01:19:27.535 line:90% position:50% align:center
“who is misleading
the entire inhabited earth;

01:19:27.535 --> 01:19:30.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
“he was hurled down to the earth,
and his angels

01:19:30.955 --> 01:19:33.874 line:90% position:50% align:center
were hurled down with him.”

01:19:33.874 --> 01:19:38.879 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, I read it that way specifically,

01:19:38.879 --> 01:19:42.550 line:90% position:50% align:center
but what it doesn’t say is

01:19:42.550 --> 01:19:44.844 line:90% position:50% align:center
(in the middle part of verse 9):

01:19:44.844 --> 01:19:49.098 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Satan, who is [trying to mislead]

01:19:49.098 --> 01:19:51.976 line:90% position:50% align:center
the entire inhabited earth.”

01:19:51.976 --> 01:19:56.355 line:90% position:50% align:center
No, he <i>“is</i>  misleading

01:19:56.355 --> 01:19:59.734 line:90% position:50% align:center
the entire inhabited earth.”

01:19:59.734 --> 01:20:04.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s crucial to understand
when we think about the theme of this talk,

01:20:04.572 --> 01:20:08.201 line:90% position:50% align:center
not to be misled by imitation peace,

01:20:08.201 --> 01:20:10.953 line:90% position:50% align:center
because as “the ruler of the world,”

01:20:10.953 --> 01:20:14.040 line:90% position:50% align:center
that’s what he’s out to do—mislead.

01:20:14.040 --> 01:20:19.045 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, it’s an interesting point
here in 2 Corinthians chapter 11

01:20:20.380 --> 01:20:22.799 line:90% position:50% align:center
to appreciate

01:20:22.799 --> 01:20:27.178 line:90% position:50% align:center
how he goes about misleading,
or at least it’s addressed here

01:20:27.178 --> 01:20:31.266 line:90% position:50% align:center
to serve as a good warning for us.

01:20:32.100 --> 01:20:35.728 line:90% position:50% align:center
And an interesting point with the revision

01:20:35.728 --> 01:20:38.273 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the <i>New World Translation</i>

01:20:38.273 --> 01:20:42.402 line:90% position:50% align:center
(for those of you in the truth before 2013

01:20:42.402 --> 01:20:45.655 line:90% position:50% align:center
when it was revised, you’ll remember this)

01:20:45.655 --> 01:20:49.868 line:90% position:50% align:center
in verse 14 of 2 Corinthians chapter 11:

01:20:49.868 --> 01:20:54.706 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And no wonder,
for Satan himself keeps disguising himself

01:20:54.706 --> 01:20:57.167 line:90% position:50% align:center
as an angel of light.”

01:20:57.167 --> 01:21:01.129 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, the <i>New World Translation</i>

01:21:01.129 --> 01:21:03.882 line:90% position:50% align:center
used to say before the revision

01:21:03.882 --> 01:21:08.261 line:90% position:50% align:center
“[transforms] himself
into an angel of light.”

01:21:08.261 --> 01:21:13.058 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, the very English word “metamorphosis,”

01:21:13.058 --> 01:21:18.063 line:90% position:50% align:center
like for a caterpillar transforming
into a beautiful butterfly,

01:21:18.063 --> 01:21:21.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
that’s where it comes from,
the Greek language.

01:21:21.316 --> 01:21:26.321 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that word was not in verse 14.

01:21:26.321 --> 01:21:30.200 line:90% position:50% align:center
No, because Satan can’t transform himself

01:21:30.200 --> 01:21:34.746 line:90% position:50% align:center
into “an angel of light”
(so it’s an improved translation),

01:21:34.746 --> 01:21:37.249 line:90% position:50% align:center
but he does disguise.

01:21:37.249 --> 01:21:39.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
He’s a masquerader.

01:21:39.668 --> 01:21:44.673 line:90% position:50% align:center
And he does that with the subject of peace.

01:21:44.673 --> 01:21:48.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
His world offers a sort of peace,

01:21:48.927 --> 01:21:52.681 line:90% position:50% align:center
but it’s imitation peace.

01:21:52.681 --> 01:21:57.019 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, Jesus is distinguished,
though, with the peace that he gives.

01:21:57.019 --> 01:21:59.229 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if you’ll follow along here

01:21:59.229 --> 01:22:02.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
in John chapter 14,

01:22:03.775 --> 01:22:06.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
he himself explains it to us.

01:22:06.111 --> 01:22:09.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we treasure the Gospel accounts,

01:22:09.573 --> 01:22:13.952 line:90% position:50% align:center
verse 27: “I leave you peace;

01:22:13.952 --> 01:22:16.705 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I give you my peace.

01:22:16.705 --> 01:22:20.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I do not give it to you
the way the world gives it.

01:22:20.459 --> 01:22:25.464 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do not let your hearts be troubled
nor let them shrink out of fear.”

01:22:25.464 --> 01:22:30.094 line:90% position:50% align:center
So Jesus gives us his peace, see.

01:22:30.094 --> 01:22:32.721 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the peace that Jesus gives us,

01:22:32.721 --> 01:22:37.726 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s this inner calm once you know
the truth and Jesus gives us the peace.

01:22:37.726 --> 01:22:42.731 line:90% position:50% align:center
We have this confidence that he loves us
and Jehovah loves us,

01:22:42.731 --> 01:22:47.444 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that we enjoy a good,
peaceful relationship with them

01:22:47.444 --> 01:22:49.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
and a good conscience.

01:22:49.572 --> 01:22:54.577 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we look forward to the Kingdom
removing all war and death.

01:22:55.411 --> 01:22:58.414 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, a point to make here:

01:22:58.414 --> 01:23:01.542 line:90% position:50% align:center
Satan wants us to trade

01:23:01.542 --> 01:23:03.919 line:90% position:50% align:center
the peace that Jesus gives

01:23:03.919 --> 01:23:07.340 line:90% position:50% align:center
for his imitation peace

01:23:07.340 --> 01:23:11.427 line:90% position:50% align:center
that he has advertised in the world.

01:23:11.427 --> 01:23:13.930 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, in this talk,

01:23:13.930 --> 01:23:18.976 line:90% position:50% align:center
we will consider
three forms of imitation peace

01:23:18.976 --> 01:23:23.981 line:90% position:50% align:center
and why the peace
that Jesus gives is superior.

01:23:25.483 --> 01:23:29.612 line:90% position:50% align:center
The first one has to do with material things

01:23:29.612 --> 01:23:32.615 line:90% position:50% align:center
—how they’ll not bring true peace.

01:23:32.615 --> 01:23:37.245 line:90% position:50% align:center
And to help us with that,
turn to Matthew chapter 4,

01:23:38.121 --> 01:23:42.500 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we’ll be referring to this chapter

01:23:42.500 --> 01:23:47.547 line:90% position:50% align:center
throughout this particular talk
about not being misled by imitation peace.

01:23:47.547 --> 01:23:50.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
And this one
is connected with material things

01:23:50.049 --> 01:23:52.051 line:90% position:50% align:center
—how they don’t bring true peace—

01:23:52.051 --> 01:23:54.595 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the example Jesus sets forth here.

01:23:54.595 --> 01:23:57.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
So in Matthew chapter 4:

01:23:57.432 --> 01:23:59.851 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then Jesus was led by the spirit

01:23:59.851 --> 01:24:03.646 line:90% position:50% align:center
“up into the wilderness
to be tempted by the Devil.

01:24:03.646 --> 01:24:07.108 line:90% position:50% align:center
“After he had fasted
for 40 days and 40 nights,

01:24:07.108 --> 01:24:09.152 line:90% position:50% align:center
“he felt hungry.

01:24:09.152 --> 01:24:12.238 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And the Tempter approached and said to him:

01:24:12.238 --> 01:24:14.699 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘If you are a son of God,

01:24:14.699 --> 01:24:17.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
tell these stones to become loaves of bread.’

01:24:18.953 --> 01:24:22.540 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But he answered: ‘It is written:

01:24:22.540 --> 01:24:25.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘“Man must live, not on bread alone,

01:24:25.877 --> 01:24:30.507 line:90% position:50% align:center
but on every word that comes
from Jehovah’s mouth.”’”

01:24:30.507 --> 01:24:33.093 line:90% position:50% align:center
Isn’t that a beautiful rebuttal?

01:24:33.093 --> 01:24:36.012 line:90% position:50% align:center
See, Jesus refused to trade

01:24:36.012 --> 01:24:40.141 line:90% position:50% align:center
his peace for material things
(in this case, bread),

01:24:40.141 --> 01:24:43.103 line:90% position:50% align:center
even though he was hungry.

01:24:43.103 --> 01:24:47.065 line:90% position:50% align:center
So serving Jehovah was more important to him

01:24:47.065 --> 01:24:49.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
than material things, see.

01:24:49.818 --> 01:24:53.113 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the world, they have this thinking,

01:24:53.113 --> 01:24:55.615 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Well, you need

01:24:55.615 --> 01:24:59.327 line:90% position:50% align:center
a certain amount of money to retire,’

01:24:59.327 --> 01:25:04.332 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they’re constantly
focused on material things

01:25:04.332 --> 01:25:07.044 line:90% position:50% align:center
—not Jesus, see.

01:25:07.044 --> 01:25:11.715 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s superior peace from Jehovah God.

01:25:11.715 --> 01:25:14.551 line:90% position:50% align:center
So it’s only temporary anyway,

01:25:14.551 --> 01:25:17.930 line:90% position:50% align:center
the material benefits that people seek

01:25:17.930 --> 01:25:21.141 line:90% position:50% align:center
and pursue throughout their lives.

01:25:21.141 --> 01:25:24.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now we can enjoy true contentment

01:25:24.645 --> 01:25:28.732 line:90% position:50% align:center
because Jehovah God is going to care for us.

01:25:28.732 --> 01:25:33.737 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know that many have
personal experiences to prove that.

01:25:33.737 --> 01:25:36.281 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, in the following video,

01:25:36.281 --> 01:25:40.536 line:90% position:50% align:center
see what a brother learned
about the so-called peace

01:25:40.536 --> 01:25:42.538 line:90% position:50% align:center
that the world promises.

01:25:48.711 --> 01:25:52.297 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a family, we were doing
very well spiritually.

01:25:52.297 --> 01:25:55.175 line:10% position:50% align:center
We did family worship, went preaching,

01:25:55.175 --> 01:25:58.178 line:10% position:50% align:center
and went to the meetings together.

01:25:59.221 --> 01:26:01.890 line:90% position:50% align:center
After some time, we began

01:26:01.890 --> 01:26:04.393 line:90% position:50% align:center
to encounter financial problems.

01:26:04.393 --> 01:26:07.563 line:90% position:50% align:center
At times, we did not even have money
to buy food

01:26:07.563 --> 01:26:09.607 line:90% position:50% align:center
for each day.

01:26:11.567 --> 01:26:14.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
Many people in our area
were going to South Africa

01:26:14.111 --> 01:26:16.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
to provide basic needs for their families.

01:26:17.239 --> 01:26:19.283 line:90% position:50% align:center
So I decided to go as well,

01:26:20.367 --> 01:26:24.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
leaving behind my wife
to take care of our seven children.

01:26:33.964 --> 01:26:35.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
This affected me spiritually

01:26:35.967 --> 01:26:39.804 line:90% position:50% align:center
because I did not know the language,
I was unable to preach,

01:26:39.804 --> 01:26:42.265 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I did not benefit from the meetings.

01:26:43.307 --> 01:26:45.393 line:90% position:50% align:center
Being so far from my family

01:26:45.393 --> 01:26:49.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
caused me to neglect
my responsibility as a family head.

01:26:50.147 --> 01:26:54.527 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a result, my family grew weak spiritually

01:26:54.527 --> 01:26:57.071 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we all missed each other very much.

01:26:57.071 --> 01:27:01.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
I realized that I had made
a wrong decision going abroad.

01:27:01.033 --> 01:27:04.787 line:90% position:50% align:center
My conscience started to trouble me greatly.

01:27:04.787 --> 01:27:07.123 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then I remembered the example of Baruch

01:27:07.123 --> 01:27:10.501 line:90% position:50% align:center
found at Jeremiah 45:5.

01:27:12.837 --> 01:27:16.299 line:90% position:50% align:center
Baruch may have wanted
to pursue material riches as I had.

01:27:18.051 --> 01:27:20.553 line:90% position:50% align:center
When he was helped, he returned.

01:27:22.180 --> 01:27:25.850 line:90% position:50% align:center
I decided then to put Jehovah in first place

01:27:25.850 --> 01:27:28.311 line:90% position:50% align:center
instead of searching for material things.

01:27:28.978 --> 01:27:32.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
So I started to make changes to go home

01:27:32.106 --> 01:27:34.275 line:90% position:50% align:center
and help my family spiritually.

01:27:36.444 --> 01:27:39.948 line:90% position:50% align:center
When I left South Africa
and reached the border of Malawi

01:27:39.948 --> 01:27:43.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
(after leaving my family
for about six months),

01:27:43.284 --> 01:27:46.621 line:90% position:50% align:center
I felt great happiness in my heart,

01:27:46.621 --> 01:27:49.207 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I am still happy till now.

01:27:50.166 --> 01:27:53.002 line:90% position:50% align:center
Studying the Bible has helped me.

01:27:53.002 --> 01:27:55.547 line:90% position:50% align:center
We still encounter financial problems,

01:27:56.548 --> 01:27:58.550 line:90% position:50% align:center
but I remember that in Satan’s world,

01:27:58.550 --> 01:28:01.594 line:90% position:50% align:center
there is nowhere we can go
and have no problems.

01:28:02.387 --> 01:28:04.556 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now I serve as an elder.

01:28:05.557 --> 01:28:07.893 line:90% position:50% align:center
My family is progressing spiritually.

01:28:09.728 --> 01:28:11.897 line:90% position:50% align:center
And this makes me very happy,

01:28:11.897 --> 01:28:15.483 line:90% position:50% align:center
because my relationship
with Jehovah is strong.

01:28:22.073 --> 01:28:26.411 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, he learned a hard lesson.

01:28:26.411 --> 01:28:28.705 line:90% position:50% align:center
He goes to South Africa

01:28:28.705 --> 01:28:33.126 line:90% position:50% align:center
—meetings interrupted and no field service.

01:28:33.126 --> 01:28:36.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then he remembers Baruch,

01:28:36.088 --> 01:28:38.965 line:90% position:50% align:center
secretary for Jeremiah.

01:28:38.965 --> 01:28:43.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
And he returns to be with his family,
putting the Kingdom first,

01:28:43.845 --> 01:28:48.350 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we appreciate him
being truthful and sharing that experience.

01:28:48.350 --> 01:28:53.105 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s imitation peace,
going after material things.

01:28:54.273 --> 01:28:58.527 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now this next one, it’s quite interesting.

01:28:58.527 --> 01:29:00.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
So pay close attention

01:29:00.529 --> 01:29:05.075 line:90% position:50% align:center
because there may be some
listening who need this counsel.

01:29:05.075 --> 01:29:07.995 line:90% position:50% align:center
Satan’s world says that we

01:29:07.995 --> 01:29:10.289 line:90% position:50% align:center
can ignore Bible standards

01:29:10.289 --> 01:29:15.294 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that we might need
to ignore some of them to gain peace of mind.

01:29:15.294 --> 01:29:19.965 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here are two examples
that we’re going to analyze in this talk.

01:29:19.965 --> 01:29:23.719 line:90% position:50% align:center
A person may reason
that marrying an unbeliever

01:29:24.845 --> 01:29:29.016 line:90% position:50% align:center
or obtaining an unscriptural divorce

01:29:29.016 --> 01:29:31.852 line:90% position:50% align:center
will make life easier.

01:29:31.852 --> 01:29:35.272 line:90% position:50% align:center
And they start reasoning this way,

01:29:35.272 --> 01:29:38.484 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I just want to get married,

01:29:38.484 --> 01:29:41.612 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he’s an unbeliever,
but he’s a nice person.’

01:29:41.612 --> 01:29:45.616 line:90% position:50% align:center
Things like that go on
with the treacherous heart.

01:29:45.616 --> 01:29:50.454 line:90% position:50% align:center
Again, we go to the example
of our Lord and Master, Jesus.

01:29:50.454 --> 01:29:55.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re going to read verses 5-7 of Matthew 4:

01:29:56.836 --> 01:30:00.715 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then the Devil took him
along into the holy city,

01:30:00.715 --> 01:30:04.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and he stationed him
on the battlement of the temple

01:30:04.135 --> 01:30:06.262 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and said to him:

01:30:06.262 --> 01:30:10.266 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘If you are a son of God,
throw yourself down,

01:30:10.266 --> 01:30:12.310 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘for it is written:

01:30:12.310 --> 01:30:15.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘“He will give his angels
a command concerning you,” 

01:30:15.688 --> 01:30:18.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘and, “They will carry you on their hands,

01:30:18.441 --> 01:30:23.029 line:90% position:50% align:center
“so that you may not strike
your foot against a stone.”’

01:30:23.029 --> 01:30:27.366 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Jesus said to him: ‘Again, it is written:

01:30:27.366 --> 01:30:31.996 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You must not put Jehovah
your God to the test.”’”

01:30:33.122 --> 01:30:36.793 line:90% position:50% align:center
See, Jesus made that very clear.

01:30:36.793 --> 01:30:39.504 line:90% position:50% align:center
He was going to be obedient to his Father

01:30:39.504 --> 01:30:43.883 line:90% position:50% align:center
and wasn’t going to worry about being testy

01:30:43.883 --> 01:30:48.763 line:90% position:50% align:center
with such an experience
as the Devil proposed there.

01:30:48.763 --> 01:30:53.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
So obedience

01:30:53.351 --> 01:30:57.981 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Jesus twice (in a moment we’ll read
another one) said: “It is written.”

01:30:57.981 --> 01:31:01.109 line:90% position:50% align:center
He sticks with the Scriptures
—Jehovah’s thinking—

01:31:01.109 --> 01:31:05.989 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he refused to disobey Jehovah.

01:31:05.989 --> 01:31:09.075 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now here’s the question,

01:31:09.075 --> 01:31:12.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why is the peace that Jesus gives

01:31:12.328 --> 01:31:14.831 line:90% position:50% align:center
superior to the pursuit

01:31:14.831 --> 01:31:19.252 line:90% position:50% align:center
of unscriptural solutions to our problems?

01:31:20.587 --> 01:31:22.630 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let that sink in.

01:31:22.630 --> 01:31:25.342 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why is the peace that Jesus gives

01:31:25.342 --> 01:31:27.594 line:90% position:50% align:center
superior to the pursuit

01:31:27.594 --> 01:31:30.639 line:90% position:50% align:center
of unscriptural solutions to our problems?

01:31:30.639 --> 01:31:33.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example, marrying an unbeliever

01:31:34.809 --> 01:31:38.897 line:90% position:50% align:center
—that will likely bring
(and it has happened time after time)

01:31:38.897 --> 01:31:41.525 line:90% position:50% align:center
that person greater pain

01:31:43.068 --> 01:31:46.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
than the longing
they felt when they were single.

01:31:46.279 --> 01:31:48.281 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’ve personally seen that

01:31:48.281 --> 01:31:52.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
all too many times in various congregations

01:31:52.285 --> 01:31:55.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
that I’ve had the privilege to serve in.

01:31:55.539 --> 01:32:00.585 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, the other one
is an unscriptural divorce.

01:32:00.585 --> 01:32:03.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
It often leads to immoral conduct.

01:32:03.797 --> 01:32:07.050 line:90% position:50% align:center
It certainly leads to a troubled conscience,

01:32:07.050 --> 01:32:11.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
emotional damage
and, of course, a loss of privileges.

01:32:13.307 --> 01:32:16.393 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, this is very important to keep in mind.

01:32:17.519 --> 01:32:22.149 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s true that with two imperfect individuals

01:32:22.149 --> 01:32:26.195 line:90% position:50% align:center
married to each other,
well, there are going to be difficulties

01:32:26.195 --> 01:32:29.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
and there are going to be challenges.

01:32:29.198 --> 01:32:32.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
But stop and think about this:

01:32:32.785 --> 01:32:35.245 line:90% position:50% align:center
When you’re having difficulties,

01:32:35.245 --> 01:32:38.207 line:90% position:50% align:center
don’t forget that marriage

01:32:38.207 --> 01:32:40.626 line:90% position:50% align:center
is a sacred arrangement.

01:32:41.752 --> 01:32:45.589 line:90% position:50% align:center
The world totally has forgotten that.

01:32:45.589 --> 01:32:49.802 line:90% position:50% align:center
So Jehovah will strengthen

01:32:49.802 --> 01:32:53.681 line:90% position:50% align:center
both to make a success.

01:32:53.681 --> 01:32:58.143 line:90% position:50% align:center
You have to keep that in mind:
Jehovah will strengthen and help

01:32:58.143 --> 01:33:02.439 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that you can succeed
because this is his sacred arrangement.

01:33:02.439 --> 01:33:06.151 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the Devil has been attacking
the family arrangement

01:33:06.151 --> 01:33:09.780 line:90% position:50% align:center
all through the last days of this system,

01:33:09.780 --> 01:33:11.866 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he’s intensifying it

01:33:11.866 --> 01:33:15.870 line:90% position:50% align:center
as he gets closer
to being thrown into the abyss.

01:33:16.996 --> 01:33:19.582 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, in the following video,

01:33:19.582 --> 01:33:24.587 line:90% position:50% align:center
notice the results
of pursuing imitation peace.

01:33:26.922 --> 01:33:28.966 line:10% position:50% align:center
Newly married life came with a lot

01:33:28.966 --> 01:33:31.260 line:10% position:50% align:center
of unexpected challenges.

01:33:31.260 --> 01:33:34.639 line:90% position:50% align:center
You dream about the way
your marriage will go,

01:33:34.639 --> 01:33:37.058 line:90% position:50% align:center
but then the reality is quite different.

01:33:40.228 --> 01:33:42.313 line:90% position:50% align:center
All we ever did was argue,

01:33:42.313 --> 01:33:44.774 line:90% position:50% align:center
or we wouldn’t speak to one another.

01:33:46.150 --> 01:33:47.860 line:90% position:50% align:center
We never ever went to the elders.

01:33:47.860 --> 01:33:49.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
We just didn’t want to bother them.

01:33:49.403 --> 01:33:52.824 line:90% position:50% align:center
We just felt, you know,
we needed to figure it out ourselves.

01:33:55.535 --> 01:33:57.745 line:90% position:50% align:center
We decided that if the house sold,

01:33:57.745 --> 01:33:59.997 line:90% position:50% align:center
then we would separate.

01:34:05.420 --> 01:34:07.422 line:90% position:50% align:center
The separation wasn’t a good thing,

01:34:07.422 --> 01:34:10.550 line:90% position:50% align:center
because in some respects
it made things worse.

01:34:11.759 --> 01:34:13.761 line:90% position:50% align:center
It did have an impact on the boys.

01:34:14.262 --> 01:34:15.346 line:90% position:50% align:center
They started acting out.

01:34:15.346 --> 01:34:19.350 line:90% position:50% align:center
They got into some trouble
with the police one time.

01:34:21.269 --> 01:34:25.315 line:90% position:50% align:center
And there was a loneliness
because you’ve gotten married,

01:34:25.315 --> 01:34:28.318 line:90% position:50% align:center
and now you don’t have that,
and you’re by yourself.

01:34:28.318 --> 01:34:31.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the same old routine
went on where you’re

01:34:31.279 --> 01:34:34.532 line:90% position:50% align:center
cooking and cleaning
and doing laundry and working.

01:34:36.367 --> 01:34:38.286 line:90% position:50% align:center
I felt sick to my stomach.

01:34:38.286 --> 01:34:42.457 line:90% position:50% align:center
I had a hard time getting up every morning
and facing the world.

01:34:42.457 --> 01:34:44.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
At that point, I felt that I needed

01:34:44.834 --> 01:34:47.420 line:90% position:50% align:center
to have the elders help out a little bit.

01:34:47.420 --> 01:34:51.508 line:90% position:50% align:center
I did pray for Jehovah’s help to direct me,

01:34:51.508 --> 01:34:54.886 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I kept wondering
why Jehovah wasn’t really

01:34:54.886 --> 01:34:56.096 line:90% position:50% align:center
answering my prayers.

01:34:56.096 --> 01:35:01.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
But I kind of realize now
that it was because we were separated.

01:35:01.101 --> 01:35:05.647 line:90% position:50% align:center
The expectations of the separation
were not at all what I was thinking.

01:35:06.565 --> 01:35:08.900 line:90% position:50% align:center
I reflected on the marriage vows.

01:35:08.900 --> 01:35:11.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
One of the things I thought about

01:35:11.069 --> 01:35:14.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
was a sister in our congregation.

01:35:14.406 --> 01:35:17.868 line:90% position:50% align:center
She was married to an unbeliever,
and then she learned the truth.

01:35:17.868 --> 01:35:20.162 line:90% position:50% align:center
And he was so violent.

01:35:20.162 --> 01:35:24.791 line:90% position:50% align:center
He would beat her; he would burn her books;
he would burn her clothes.

01:35:24.791 --> 01:35:27.711 line:90% position:50% align:center
He did not allow her children
to attend the meetings.

01:35:27.711 --> 01:35:30.589 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I thought about the problems
that Darrel and I had.

01:35:30.589 --> 01:35:32.799 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I thought:
‘Well, Darrel is a kind person.

01:35:32.799 --> 01:35:34.051 line:90% position:50% align:center
He’s never done that.’

01:35:34.051 --> 01:35:35.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I thought:

01:35:35.510 --> 01:35:37.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘You know, this is something

01:35:37.095 --> 01:35:38.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘that we need to really work on.

01:35:38.430 --> 01:35:41.975 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘We need to really put forth the effort

01:35:41.975 --> 01:35:44.061 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘to start applying Bible principles

01:35:44.645 --> 01:35:46.605 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘to put Jehovah first in our life

01:35:46.605 --> 01:35:50.150 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that we can bring our marriage
back in union with Jehovah.’

01:35:51.485 --> 01:35:55.113 line:90% position:50% align:center
I realized that it wasn’t what I wanted,

01:35:55.113 --> 01:35:57.366 line:90% position:50% align:center
but it was what Jehovah wanted.

01:36:00.744 --> 01:36:02.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
There was just no other choice.

01:36:02.955 --> 01:36:06.792 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah wasn’t going to bless us
unless we got back together.

01:36:07.960 --> 01:36:12.589 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we got back together,
our marriage was still a work in progress.

01:36:12.589 --> 01:36:14.591 line:90% position:50% align:center
You can’t have
a perfect marriage in this world,

01:36:14.591 --> 01:36:18.345 line:90% position:50% align:center
but you can sure make it better
when you put Jehovah first.

01:36:18.345 --> 01:36:20.681 line:90% position:50% align:center
We enjoyed the feelings
we had toward each other.

01:36:20.681 --> 01:36:22.891 line:90% position:50% align:center
I felt closer to Debbie.

01:36:25.436 --> 01:36:27.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
Debbie and I
have been married now for 48 years.

01:36:27.688 --> 01:36:31.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
Separation does not make
anything better at all.

01:36:31.901 --> 01:36:35.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
If you even have an inkling of love
for one another,

01:36:35.112 --> 01:36:38.616 line:90% position:50% align:center
you want to work on that,
and you want to make it bloom

01:36:38.616 --> 01:36:40.618 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that Jehovah can bless it.

01:36:40.618 --> 01:36:42.661 line:90% position:50% align:center
The blessings have been endless.

01:36:42.661 --> 01:36:44.663 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our children are all doing

01:36:44.663 --> 01:36:47.291 line:90% position:50% align:center
fantastic in the truth.

01:36:47.291 --> 01:36:49.585 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah said:
“Taste and see that [He] is good.”

01:36:49.585 --> 01:36:51.712 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we’ve got to do that.

01:36:57.635 --> 01:37:01.764 line:90% position:50% align:center
We really appreciated this couple sharing

01:37:01.764 --> 01:37:05.142 line:90% position:50% align:center
their experience with the brotherhood.

01:37:05.142 --> 01:37:07.562 line:90% position:50% align:center
He learned, you know.

01:37:07.562 --> 01:37:09.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
They were always arguing,

01:37:09.564 --> 01:37:13.276 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that’s all they
did was argue, argue, argue.

01:37:13.276 --> 01:37:16.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
It affected their children.

01:37:16.112 --> 01:37:20.741 line:90% position:50% align:center
They decided to separate
and finally have peace.

01:37:20.741 --> 01:37:24.996 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I don’t have to be around her,’
or ‘I don’t have to be around him.’

01:37:24.996 --> 01:37:28.958 line:90% position:50% align:center
But then he realized
his relationship with Jehovah

01:37:28.958 --> 01:37:31.753 line:90% position:50% align:center
was being interfered with here,

01:37:31.753 --> 01:37:34.672 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he went to the elders.

01:37:34.672 --> 01:37:36.674 line:90% position:50% align:center
His prayers were affected.

01:37:36.674 --> 01:37:39.427 line:90% position:50% align:center
The things he noticed
—he was honest about that.

01:37:39.427 --> 01:37:44.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
And our precious sister
was so nice to honestly explain.

01:37:44.182 --> 01:37:48.728 line:90% position:50% align:center
She said what she learned
was that ‘this is not about me;

01:37:48.728 --> 01:37:51.147 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s about Jehovah.’

01:37:51.147 --> 01:37:54.484 line:90% position:50% align:center
When you finally come to that realization,

01:37:54.484 --> 01:37:56.694 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah will strengthen you

01:37:56.694 --> 01:38:00.615 line:90% position:50% align:center
to enjoy peace with your marriage partner.

01:38:01.783 --> 01:38:06.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, the next one, I never tire of speaking

01:38:06.287 --> 01:38:11.292 line:90% position:50% align:center
about these particular couple of verses

01:38:11.292 --> 01:38:15.964 line:90% position:50% align:center
or reading about it or hearing
another brother give a talk about it.

01:38:15.964 --> 01:38:18.425 line:90% position:50% align:center
See, here’s what’s coming soon.

01:38:18.425 --> 01:38:22.178 line:90% position:50% align:center
Turn with me to 1 Thessalonians chapter 5.

01:38:22.178 --> 01:38:25.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
And many of you are going, ‘Oh, yeah, I know

01:38:25.932 --> 01:38:28.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
what he’s going to read about.’

01:38:28.351 --> 01:38:32.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
And this is one of the prophecies

01:38:32.564 --> 01:38:35.817 line:90% position:50% align:center
that is yet to be fulfilled.

01:38:35.817 --> 01:38:38.153 line:90% position:50% align:center
So it’s just invigorating

01:38:38.153 --> 01:38:41.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
to know that soon
here’s what’s going to happen

01:38:41.573 --> 01:38:44.326 line:90% position:50% align:center
—1 Thessalonians chapter 5,

01:38:45.827 --> 01:38:48.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
verses 2 and 3:

01:38:48.038 --> 01:38:52.000 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For you yourselves know very well

01:38:52.000 --> 01:38:57.005 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that Jehovah’s day
is coming exactly as a thief in the night.

01:38:58.256 --> 01:39:00.801 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Whenever it is that they are saying,

01:39:00.801 --> 01:39:04.304 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Peace and security!’

01:39:04.304 --> 01:39:09.184 line:90% position:50% align:center
“then sudden destruction
is to be instantly on them,

01:39:09.184 --> 01:39:13.146 line:90% position:50% align:center
“just like birth pains on a pregnant woman,

01:39:13.146 --> 01:39:17.234 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they will by no means escape.”

01:39:18.694 --> 01:39:21.738 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, see, “Jehovah’s day”

01:39:21.738 --> 01:39:26.368 line:90% position:50% align:center
—this has to do with the day
of the outbreak of the great tribulation

01:39:26.368 --> 01:39:29.580 line:90% position:50% align:center
when Babylon the Great is destroyed

01:39:29.580 --> 01:39:31.915 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Armageddon finishes it off.

01:39:31.915 --> 01:39:35.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this context, that’s “Jehovah’s day.”

01:39:35.127 --> 01:39:38.130 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what happens before then

01:39:38.130 --> 01:39:42.551 line:90% position:50% align:center
is this proclamation, “peace and security!”

01:39:42.551 --> 01:39:45.262 line:90% position:50% align:center
Will religious leaders be involved?

01:39:45.262 --> 01:39:49.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, they’re part of Satan’s system;
that’s very possible.

01:39:49.099 --> 01:39:50.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll have to wait and see.

01:39:50.351 --> 01:39:54.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
Will it be one announcement
or a series of announcements?

01:39:54.688 --> 01:39:56.690 line:90% position:50% align:center
That we don’t know.

01:39:56.690 --> 01:39:58.692 line:90% position:50% align:center
But this is coming.

01:39:58.692 --> 01:40:02.530 line:90% position:50% align:center
And those who are staying close to Jehovah

01:40:02.530 --> 01:40:06.283 line:90% position:50% align:center
and enjoying the peace
from him and his Son, Jesus,

01:40:06.283 --> 01:40:08.786 line:90% position:50% align:center
will not be deceived

01:40:08.786 --> 01:40:12.873 line:90% position:50% align:center
by this imitation proclamation of peace

01:40:12.873 --> 01:40:15.418 line:90% position:50% align:center
—imitation peace.

01:40:15.418 --> 01:40:20.089 line:90% position:50% align:center
And again, back in Matthew chapter 4,

01:40:20.089 --> 01:40:23.801 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’re going to see how Jesus handled

01:40:23.801 --> 01:40:26.554 line:90% position:50% align:center
this type of test from the Devil

01:40:26.554 --> 01:40:28.931 line:90% position:50% align:center
and what we learn from it here

01:40:28.931 --> 01:40:33.144 line:90% position:50% align:center
in verses 8-11 of Matthew chapter 4.

01:40:35.104 --> 01:40:38.024 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Again the Devil took him [in verse 8]

01:40:38.024 --> 01:40:41.486 line:90% position:50% align:center
“along to an unusually high mountain

01:40:41.486 --> 01:40:46.032 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and showed him all the kingdoms
of the world and their glory.

01:40:46.032 --> 01:40:48.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And he said to him:

01:40:48.409 --> 01:40:51.454 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘All these things I will give you

01:40:51.454 --> 01:40:55.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
“if you fall down
and do an act of worship to me.’

01:40:57.001 --> 01:41:00.421 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then Jesus said to him [without hesitation]:

01:41:00.421 --> 01:41:02.882 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Go away, Satan!

01:41:02.882 --> 01:41:07.512 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘For it is written:
“It is Jehovah your God you must worship,

01:41:07.512 --> 01:41:12.016 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it is to him alone
you must render sacred service.”’

01:41:13.101 --> 01:41:17.105 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then the Devil left him,
and look! angels came

01:41:17.105 --> 01:41:19.732 line:90% position:50% align:center
and began to minister to him.”

01:41:20.900 --> 01:41:24.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
Right away, a third time: “It is written.”

01:41:24.487 --> 01:41:27.866 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus was having nothing to do

01:41:27.866 --> 01:41:32.036 line:90% position:50% align:center
with this offer of the kingdoms
—this imitation peace.

01:41:32.036 --> 01:41:35.999 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘You’ll have all the glory and rule.’

01:41:35.999 --> 01:41:39.210 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it’s always boggled my mind

01:41:39.210 --> 01:41:42.630 line:90% position:50% align:center
that this one who knew

01:41:42.630 --> 01:41:45.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus in his prehuman existence

01:41:45.634 --> 01:41:50.597 line:90% position:50% align:center
would have the audacity to try to get Jesus
to bow down and worship him.

01:41:50.597 --> 01:41:55.602 line:90% position:50% align:center
It shows you that he’s obviously insane.

01:41:57.020 --> 01:42:00.065 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, he wouldn’t allow it either

01:42:00.065 --> 01:42:02.484 line:90% position:50% align:center
when they tried to make him an earthly king.

01:42:02.484 --> 01:42:05.028 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus wasn’t having any part of that.

01:42:05.028 --> 01:42:08.281 line:90% position:50% align:center
They were thinking he could bring them peace.

01:42:08.281 --> 01:42:13.286 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Jesus said there’s no peace
except by Jehovah’s way.

01:42:14.162 --> 01:42:18.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the peace from God’s Kingdom
is so superior

01:42:18.583 --> 01:42:23.588 line:90% position:50% align:center
to anything they could try to come up with
—their imitation peace.

01:42:24.297 --> 01:42:25.424 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here’s why.

01:42:25.424 --> 01:42:27.426 line:90% position:50% align:center
Think about this:

01:42:28.969 --> 01:42:31.305 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus will remove the Devil.

01:42:33.056 --> 01:42:36.768 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus will remove human rulership.

01:42:36.768 --> 01:42:39.271 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus will remove sin.

01:42:40.439 --> 01:42:45.444 line:90% position:50% align:center
So the earth’s peace
will never again be disturbed.

01:42:47.070 --> 01:42:51.825 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I appreciate very much
that he’s going to get rid of all problems,

01:42:51.825 --> 01:42:56.288 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that includes undoing all causes of pain

01:42:56.288 --> 01:42:59.333 line:90% position:50% align:center
—and not just physical pain,

01:42:59.333 --> 01:43:02.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
emotional pain as well.

01:43:03.629 --> 01:43:08.008 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s wonderful to look forward to that time

01:43:08.008 --> 01:43:10.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
with that beautiful peace

01:43:10.260 --> 01:43:13.722 line:90% position:50% align:center
from our precious Father,
Jehovah, and his Son, Jesus.

01:43:13.722 --> 01:43:16.809 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, in the following video,

01:43:16.809 --> 01:43:19.144 line:90% position:50% align:center
see what convinced this sister

01:43:19.144 --> 01:43:24.149 line:90% position:50% align:center
not to believe the world’s promises of peace.

01:43:28.529 --> 01:43:31.574 line:90% position:50% align:center
My father always taught me
that we needed God in our life

01:43:31.574 --> 01:43:33.617 line:90% position:50% align:center
in order for there to be peace.

01:43:36.328 --> 01:43:38.414 line:10% position:50% align:center
And he always wanted to know,

01:43:38.414 --> 01:43:40.458 line:10% position:50% align:center
Can Christians go to war?

01:43:41.709 --> 01:43:45.796 line:90% position:50% align:center
How is this consistent
with the Gospel of Jesus Christ?

01:43:46.464 --> 01:43:49.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
But the pastor could never give us an answer,

01:43:49.967 --> 01:43:53.429 line:90% position:50% align:center
and so I thought I’d have to look
to politics to find it.

01:43:53.429 --> 01:43:56.891 line:90% position:50% align:center
A lot of peace movements
were being formed at that time,

01:43:56.891 --> 01:43:58.935 line:90% position:50% align:center
so I joined one of them.

01:44:00.728 --> 01:44:03.606 line:90% position:50% align:center
We decided where
the protest marches would be

01:44:03.606 --> 01:44:05.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
and which pamphlets we would use.

01:44:09.278 --> 01:44:11.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
But after the protests were over,

01:44:11.864 --> 01:44:14.242 line:90% position:50% align:center
everyone was so excited

01:44:14.242 --> 01:44:16.536 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they all started applauding

01:44:16.536 --> 01:44:18.579 line:90% position:50% align:center
and cheering for the leaders.

01:44:18.579 --> 01:44:22.041 line:90% position:50% align:center
I thought:
‘That’s not what I wanted.

01:44:22.041 --> 01:44:24.335 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I don’t want to honor people.

01:44:24.335 --> 01:44:27.547 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I want to have world peace.

01:44:27.547 --> 01:44:29.799 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that still hasn’t happened yet.’

01:44:34.470 --> 01:44:37.640 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then I started to feel very alone,

01:44:37.640 --> 01:44:40.643 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it made me feel unsafe in this world.

01:44:40.643 --> 01:44:42.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
With no peace in sight,

01:44:42.645 --> 01:44:45.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
I thought,
‘What is the purpose of life?’

01:44:46.691 --> 01:44:50.737 line:90% position:50% align:center
While visiting friends for coffee,
I saw a man I’d never met before.

01:44:52.489 --> 01:44:55.700 line:90% position:50% align:center
My friends told me he wanted
to talk to us about the Bible.

01:44:58.912 --> 01:45:00.705 line:90% position:50% align:center
So I asked him:

01:45:00.705 --> 01:45:02.665 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Sir, what do you think?

01:45:02.665 --> 01:45:04.751 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can Christians join the military?”

01:45:05.752 --> 01:45:08.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the man said,
“No, that’s not allowed

01:45:08.380 --> 01:45:11.174 line:90% position:50% align:center
because the Bible says
you should ‘love your [enemy].’”

01:45:14.135 --> 01:45:16.596 line:90% position:50% align:center
It made me think
about what my father always said

01:45:17.389 --> 01:45:19.849 line:90% position:50% align:center
—that we need God to bring peace.

01:45:23.478 --> 01:45:25.480 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then a really nice lady came to my door,

01:45:25.480 --> 01:45:27.524 line:90% position:50% align:center
and she had an orange book in her hand.

01:45:28.942 --> 01:45:31.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it said:
<i>True Peace and Security.</i>

01:45:35.699 --> 01:45:37.826 line:90% position:50% align:center
After reading it, I thought:

01:45:37.826 --> 01:45:39.870 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘This is it!

01:45:39.870 --> 01:45:43.123 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is the organization
that truly wants peace.’

01:45:45.959 --> 01:45:49.004 line:90% position:50% align:center
So I went to those involved
in the peace movement.

01:45:50.505 --> 01:45:53.508 line:90% position:50% align:center
I told them that I believe
that God will change this world

01:45:53.508 --> 01:45:56.887 line:90% position:50% align:center
into a beautiful earth
where there’ll be true peace.

01:45:58.347 --> 01:46:01.141 line:90% position:50% align:center
They all looked at me
like I had lost my mind.

01:46:02.017 --> 01:46:04.686 line:90% position:50% align:center
I was so happy with my new life.

01:46:04.686 --> 01:46:06.521 line:90% position:50% align:center
I felt like I was part of a family

01:46:06.521 --> 01:46:08.565 line:90% position:50% align:center
who truly cared about one another

01:46:08.565 --> 01:46:11.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
and really wanted peace with each other.

01:46:15.447 --> 01:46:19.618 line:90% position:50% align:center
Isaiah 14:7 had a major impact on my life

01:46:19.618 --> 01:46:21.829 line:90% position:50% align:center
because there God promises

01:46:21.829 --> 01:46:24.706 line:90% position:50% align:center
a calm and peaceful world.

01:46:33.882 --> 01:46:37.428 line:90% position:50% align:center
Wasn’t that nice how she learned?

01:46:37.428 --> 01:46:42.016 line:90% position:50% align:center
She’d looked to politics and protests
for world peace.

01:46:42.016 --> 01:46:44.560 line:90% position:50% align:center
Obviously, she was sincere.

01:46:44.560 --> 01:46:49.398 line:90% position:50% align:center
But she learned that’s all imitation peace.

01:46:49.398 --> 01:46:54.028 line:90% position:50% align:center
True peace and security
comes from Jehovah God.

01:46:55.529 --> 01:47:00.201 line:90% position:50% align:center
So wrapping it up with these
three different types

01:47:00.201 --> 01:47:03.829 line:90% position:50% align:center
of imitation peace
that we’ve emphasized,

01:47:03.829 --> 01:47:08.501 line:90% position:50% align:center
we want to encourage you
in these last minutes

01:47:08.501 --> 01:47:13.506 line:90% position:50% align:center
to safeguard the peace
that Jesus has given you.

01:47:15.299 --> 01:47:17.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
In John chapter 14

01:47:20.680 --> 01:47:23.933 line:90% position:50% align:center
(you know this,
but I want you to really focus

01:47:23.933 --> 01:47:28.187 line:90% position:50% align:center
on a particular point), in verse 6:

01:47:30.022 --> 01:47:32.024 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Jesus said to him:

01:47:32.024 --> 01:47:36.612 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘I am the way and the truth and the life.

01:47:36.612 --> 01:47:41.617 line:90% position:50% align:center
No one comes to the Father
except through me.’”

01:47:41.617 --> 01:47:43.619 line:90% position:50% align:center
Isn’t that beautiful?

01:47:44.912 --> 01:47:49.917 line:90% position:50% align:center
Particularly we want to emphasize
Jesus is “the truth.”

01:47:51.836 --> 01:47:54.172 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can trust all of his promises.

01:47:54.172 --> 01:47:56.382 line:90% position:50% align:center
He is “the truth.”

01:47:57.884 --> 01:48:00.928 line:90% position:50% align:center
He’s going to give us peace
—already has—

01:48:00.928 --> 01:48:05.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
and will to a greater extent in the future.

01:48:05.099 --> 01:48:08.561 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, our Master is “the truth.”

01:48:08.561 --> 01:48:12.357 line:90% position:50% align:center
And he gave the early Christians that peace.

01:48:12.357 --> 01:48:15.652 line:90% position:50% align:center
The things that they were able to deal
with are just mind-boggling.

01:48:15.652 --> 01:48:20.657 line:90% position:50% align:center
As we read the apostle Paul’s experiences
and Peter’s and others’

01:48:20.657 --> 01:48:24.244 line:90% position:50% align:center
—the persecution they endured—
they did it,

01:48:24.244 --> 01:48:27.080 line:90% position:50% align:center
enduring with joy.

01:48:27.080 --> 01:48:28.498 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s amazing!

01:48:28.498 --> 01:48:33.503 line:90% position:50% align:center
It can only be
a supernatural provision of peace.

01:48:33.503 --> 01:48:35.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
And just remember,

01:48:35.755 --> 01:48:40.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus will likewise give you
the peace you need now

01:48:40.510 --> 01:48:45.515 line:90% position:50% align:center
to keep doing Jehovah’s will
and to make Him happy.

01:48:45.515 --> 01:48:48.560 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, brothers, please,

01:48:49.895 --> 01:48:53.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
safeguard the gift of peace

01:48:53.190 --> 01:48:56.401 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jesus has given you.

01:48:56.401 --> 01:48:59.488 line:90% position:50% align:center
Satan uses this world

01:48:59.488 --> 01:49:03.200 line:90% position:50% align:center
to offer you promises of imitation peace.

01:49:03.200 --> 01:49:05.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do not be misled!

01:49:06.995 --> 01:49:11.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
No, rather, “Let the peace of the Christ
rule in your hearts.”

01:49:11.583 --> 01:49:14.002 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And show yourselves thankful.”

01:49:14.002 --> 01:49:16.004 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, through his Son,

01:49:16.004 --> 01:49:20.842 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah will bless us all with peace forever!

01:49:22.636 --> 01:49:26.556 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you, Brother Morris,
for strengthening our trust in Jesus’ promise

01:49:26.556 --> 01:49:31.562 line:90% position:50% align:center
to give us peace now and during the events
that will shortly take place.

01:49:32.938 --> 01:49:36.400 line:90% position:50% align:center
The second session of our convention
has truly helped us 

01:49:36.400 --> 01:49:40.070 line:90% position:50% align:center
to see how Jehovah blesses us with peace.

01:49:41.280 --> 01:49:45.325 line:90% position:50% align:center
What can we look forward to
in the next session?

01:49:45.325 --> 01:49:49.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
The scripture theme will be
from 2 Peter 3:14:

01:49:49.955 --> 01:49:54.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Be found . . . spotless and unblemished
and in peace.”

01:49:55.419 --> 01:49:59.506 line:90% position:50% align:center
The program will begin with a symposium
that will help prepare us

01:49:59.506 --> 01:50:03.719 line:90% position:50% align:center
to share the “good news of peace”
at every opportunity.

01:50:05.179 --> 01:50:09.558 line:90% position:50% align:center
Young ones can look forward
to a special talk just for them

01:50:09.558 --> 01:50:12.061 line:90% position:50% align:center
given by a member of the Governing Body.

01:50:13.646 --> 01:50:17.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll also see how brothers and sisters
are maintaining their peace

01:50:17.942 --> 01:50:21.779 line:90% position:50% align:center
even when suffering from illness,
economic problems,

01:50:21.779 --> 01:50:26.325 line:90% position:50% align:center
natural disasters, and other difficulties.

01:50:26.325 --> 01:50:31.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
And of course, our next session
includes the baptism talk,

01:50:31.038 --> 01:50:33.457 line:90% position:50% align:center
after which those who have been approved

01:50:33.457 --> 01:50:36.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
will be baptized locally.

01:50:36.293 --> 01:50:38.921 line:90% position:50% align:center
We have much to look forward to!

01:50:40.631 --> 01:50:42.633 line:90% position:50% align:center
To conclude today’s session,

01:50:42.633 --> 01:50:46.053 line:90% position:50% align:center
let’s sing song number 112, entitled

01:50:46.053 --> 01:50:48.556 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Jehovah, God of Peace.”

01:50:48.556 --> 01:50:52.226 line:90% position:50% align:center
Again, that’s song number 112.

01:50:52.226 --> 01:50:56.480 line:90% position:50% align:center
After the song concludes,
you may have your own closing prayer.

